title: cranberry delight salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in hot water.
Then add crushed pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Stir until mixture is evenly distributed. Refrigerate until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat with mixer.
Add chocolate syrup and nuts. Pour into cookie sheet with sides.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: southern delight dessert
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Combine last four ingredients and spread over cooled cake.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into first mixture.
Bake in 3 pans at 350°.

title: red letter day casserole
directions: *Leftover potatoes or even hash browns will do fine.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Between two sheets of plastic wrap, flatten 2 boneless skinless chicken breasts to double their size.
Season chicken with a pinch of salt, pepper and dried basil.
Dust chicken with flour, patting firmly on both sides.

title: one-pot buckaroo stew
directions: Put altogether in a pan and cook for 2 hours at 350° in the oven.

title: butter bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Chill before serving.

title: spaghetti
directions: In pan, cook ground meat until well browned. Cook the spaghetti according to package directions.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water, stewed tomatoes, garlic powder, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper to taste to ground meat.
Cover and cook 1 hour. Drain spaghetti.
Leave in pan.
Put spaghetti in dishes.
Pour sauce over spaghetti.

title: noodle medley
directions: Melt shortening.
Saute meat and vegetables until lightly brown.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn to simmer for about 20 minutes or until noodles are done.
Serve with French bread and tossed green salad.

title: elaine's taco dip
directions: Mix in food processor the cottage cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on small cookie sheet or similar tray. Select vegies you like and chop very fine.
Put on top of dip in rows about 2 inches wide.
Also, make a row or 2 of Mozzarella. Serve with tortilla or corn chips for dipping.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes approximately 3 pounds (20 servings).

title: marinated green beans
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: toffee candy
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Heat until boiling, stirring constantly, 10 to 12 minutes.
Grease pan.
Sprinkle with nuts. Pour hot mixture over nuts in thin sheets.
When set, but still warm, break chocolate bars over mixture and let melt.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Brown and season chops.
Place in casserole dish and cover with mushroom soup.
Pour milk to cover.
Top with cornflakes or bran flakes.
Bake at 325° to 350° until meat is tender to prick of a fork, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
The milk seems to have a tenderizing effect.

title: 1,2,3,4 cake
directions: Cream shortening well.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat for 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat on high speed for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° in pound cake pan or in layer pans until comes from edge of pan.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in large container.
In saucepan, combine the oleo, celery salt, onion powder, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke and bring to boil.
Pour over cereals and mix easily, but well.
Place mixture in baking pans not over two layers deep; bake at 275° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in cans.

title: kathy's butterscotch bars(makes 5 to 6 dozen)
directions: Combine 1/4 cup Crisco, butterscotch chips, peanut butter and milk in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir occasionally until mixture is melted and smooth.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine cornflakes and margarine; mix well.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fool's pie
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
In bowl, cream sugar, milk, flour and fruit juice.
Pour over butter (do not stir).
Drop fruit
on top of mixture (do not mix).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Top with vanilla ice cream.
Enjoy.

title: easy rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast on lukewarm water. Add other ingredients in order given. Beat until well blended. Dough may be rolled out immediately or stored in a Tupperware bowl in refrigerator for up to 3 days. This recipe makes great cinnamon or dinner rolls. Allow to rise 1 1/2 hours before baking in a 350° oven.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook for about 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: casserole baked corn
directions: Chop onion, pepper and pimiento.
Add corn and other ingredients; place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until when you shake it, it is almost firm.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat just until stiff, pour quickly into 6 x 8-inch pan. Do not overbeat.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 small or 1 large pie shell.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: harvest pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water for 4 minutes. Add Brussels sprouts and carrots; cook an additional 9 to 11 minutes or until pasta and vegetables are of desired doneness. Drain; return to pot. Keep covered.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart ring mold. Set in pan of hot water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Fill center with cooked peas and sauteed mushrooms.
Serve with egg sauce.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix tuna, egg, crackers, salt and pepper.
Make into small patties.
Fry in hot grease until slightly browned.
Good served with hush puppies and tartar sauce.

title: golden coin carrot salad
directions: Slice and cook carrots in salted water.
When tender, drain and cool.
Arrange in layers with sliced pepper and onion.
Cover with sauce and marinate overnight in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture gathers on the stirring spoon and forms dough.
This will take about 6 minutes.
Dump onto waxed paper until cool enough to handle and knead to form a pliable mass.
Store in covered container or plastic bag.
Food coloring may be added to make colored play dough.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: peanut pudding
directions: With a pastry cutter, blend flour and margarine.
Add chopped nuts and pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: vivian's chocolate cake
directions: *To make sour milk:
Take 1/4 cup of vinegar, then fill cup to 2/3 more with milk.

title: 7-up salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch dish, heat pineapple and applesauce; dissolve Jell-O in this mixture and let cool, then add 7-Up and pecans. Let set and serve.
The size of cans may vary; size near amount will do.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix corns, salt, sour cream and Jiffy mix in large bowl.
Melt margarine and pour into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour mix over margarine and bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and serve.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Saute garlic in oil until tender.
Add water; mix.
Add bread cubes; mix.
Discard garlic.
Spread cubes on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook hamburg in deep pan until browned.
Drain excess fat. Add onions through mushrooms.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes until onions are soft.
Cook shells and drain.

title: egg custard
directions: Add sugar to well beaten eggs and beat again.
Add other ingredients and beat again.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes. Lower oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until "settled."
Feel consistency of "settled" with touching.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer over low heat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
(Requires a large amount.)
Refrigerate or let stand for several hours before serving.
Mixture will thicken as it sits.
Serves 2 to 3 main dishes or 4 to 6 side dishes.

title: doodle cake
directions: Stir well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: mary crowley's yummy cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and butter or oleo; let this stand for 10 to 20 minutes.
Mix with other ingredients; stir gently.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Roll crackers fine and mix well with nuts.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add baking powder and beat until very stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Fold crackers, nuts and vanilla into egg whites. Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate shavings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: moist banana bundt cake
directions: In blender, add bananas, hot water and soda.
Mix until a thick liquid.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add flour and banana mixture alternately.
Add nuts and bake in well-greased Bundt pan in a 350° oven for 70 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Sift and measure flour.
Add shortening and cut in until like cornmeal.
Add milk all at once and stir with fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Fold over in half and roll lightly again, about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
(Folding dough in half and cutting makes the biscuits "pop" open to insert sausage, ham, etc.)

title: cannelloni magnifique
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add spinach (which has been cooked and drained), 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasonings and mix well.
Fill noodles with mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese and continue baking uncovered until cheese is melted.
Magnifique!

title: creole snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in large bowl.
Add soup and salad dressing mix.
Add flour slowly to make stiff dough, beating well.
Knead on floured surface until elastic.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes until doubled in bulk.
Divide dough into 4 loaves.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Cover.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then mix the remaining ingredients.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix biscuit mix, potato flakes and sugar.
Add margarine, egg and flavoring.
Make into small balls.
Pat down with fork.
Leave room for cookie to spread when putting on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light brown on edges. Let cool on cookie sheet before removing.

title: macaroni-tuna bake
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, stirring until smooth. Stir in milk, blending well.
Simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, mustard and cheese, blending well. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: guess again casserole
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until tender.
Drain. Mash carrots in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs; mix well.
Pour in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's jelly pudding pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Then add flour, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Fold in egg whites last.
Pour into two unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until done, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins, nuts and fruit cocktail; mix by hand. Add reserved juice if needed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 9 x 12-inch pan or tube pan.
When cake cools, add topping.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Combine flour and beer in a large bowl and blend thoroughly using a rotary beater.
Cover; allow batter to stand at room temperature for at least 3 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Arrange chopped chicken in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan heat soup and cream cheese until mixed.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crackers and poppy seed and sprinkle over soup mixture.
Drizzle margarine over the crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly and slightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken breasts diane(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In a microwave-safe dish, melt butter and mix with oil.
Place chicken in dish, coating on both sides.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Let rest 1 minute. Turn breasts over.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes until done. Do not overcook.

title: rick's delight
directions: Brown ground meat and onion along with pepper and salt.
Stir in soup.
Let cook about 10 minutes.
At the very end, stir in 1 cup of sour cream.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten rolls in 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan and bake as directions on can.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing. Spread this on crust and top with shredded carrots, chopped broccoli and cauliflower.
Add 2 cups shredded cheese (any kind). Refrigerate.

title: split pea soup
directions: Remove butt; add peas and 1 quart water.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut butt in pieces; add to soup with celery, carrots and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, approximately 1/2 hour. Add potatoes; cook until potatoes are cooked.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix crushed 1 1/2 cups cornflakes and margarine.
Spread evenly into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Put in cabbage, then onion on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle salt.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together like pie crust.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Meanwhile, combine ingredients following and beat well.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes more.
Sprinkle powdered sugar upon removing from oven.
This is better if it is allowed to sit a day before cutting into squares.

title: yum yum chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan, boil sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and corn syrup. Cook 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot on ice cream or cake. Keeps in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain well.
Add chopped veggies.
Layer pasta, veggies, Salad Supreme and pour oil and vinegar dressing (Italian) over each layer and stir.
Do not use fat-free dressing!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add egg yolks, milk, vanilla and then butter.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend milk, cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour into dish lined with vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: potdam
directions: Break up the meat; add seasonings and brown lightly.
Layer meat, potatoes, onions, beans and catsup, beginning and ending with meat.
Top with slices of bacon.
Cover and bake at 375° for at least 60 minutes.
Uncover and bake until potatoes test done. Serves 6.

title: lipton's meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in catsup, water, onion soup mix and bread crumbs or oatmeal.
Mix well with ground beef.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix well and lay in 9-inch spring pan.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, place thinly sliced potatoes and chopped onion.
Add half the cheese, then the hamburger and top with remaining cheese.
Mix seasonings with tomato sauce and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and oil.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into a ball the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with back of spoon or your hand. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: old fashioned irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients over butter and cut in well.
Add raisins and seeds, mix well.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Put into a pan.
Make the sign of the cross in the top of loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried goat or beef
directions: Marinate mutton or beef overnight with chives, onions, salt, pepper, parsley and celery; stir occasionally.
In a large, heavy pot, heat the oil and saute the curry powder and cumin over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add the meat and all the marinade and sear the meat all over in the hot oil.
Add 1 quart of water and bring to a boil.
Cover; lower the heat and simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally and add more water if the meat starts to dry.
Serve with hot rice.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix together chopped pecans and coconut.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts with coconut.

title: wallpaper remover
directions: You will need a pan or large bowl, plastic scraper and sponge.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in quart jar (or larger).
Shake until mixed.
Pour desired amount over your favorite salad greens and serve.

title: grandma's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend dry mixture and shortening using your fingers.
Add buttermilk and mix quickly (may take more or less, depending on thickness of buttermilk).
Dough should not be too dry or sticky.
Turn out on floured surface; sprinkle flour on top and pat to 1/2-inch thick with hands.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 biscuits.

title: peanut butter oat cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats. In large bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Beat in sugars until blended. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture; mix until well combined. Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten slightly with a fork. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden. Cool on a wire rack. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: canned pickled beets
directions: Boil whole beats with 1 inch top stem and all of the root for about 45 minutes, or longer according to the amount of beets in the container.
Drain off hot water and add cold water.
Slip off the skins and slice or quarter the beets, however desired.
Add equal amounts of vinegar, sugar & water.
Put all of this over your beets and add 3 Tbsp. pickling spices that has been tied in a cloth into the solution.
Bring to boil and boil slowly for about 15-20 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars with beets, then fill jars with beet juice.
Be sure it is over top of the beets.
Cover with lids that have been sterilized and seal jars.

title: french roll-ups
directions: Beat eggs long enough to mix yolks and whites.
Add flour and salt and stir again until batter is smooth.
Combine milk and salad oil.
Stir into egg mixture until batter looks like heavy cream.
Pour batter from cup or pitcher onto hot griddle.
When little bubbles show, turn and brown on other side.
Spread with jelly or preserves; roll up like tube and serve.
Can sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: caesar salad
directions: Whisk the first 6 ingredients together, then add coddled egg (place broken egg into hot water for 15 to 20 seconds) and lemon juice.
Whisk again.
Pour over romaine lettuce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate; mix well.
Sift together cake flour and baking powder and add alternately to the creamed mixture with the buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour mixture into 3 well-greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
When cool, frost with White Frosting.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and heat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Requires very little beating.
Quickly stir in walnuts; turn into buttered pan. Let set until firm before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: loretta's dill pickles
directions: In sterilized jars, pack pickles, dill and garlic.
(The amount varies by what you prefer; I put in 1 large sprig of dill and 4 cloves of garlic per pint.)
Heat brine until boiling; pour over pickles and let stand until warm.
The drain pickles, reheat brine and refill jars.
(This will keep the pickles crisp.)
Seal with sterilized lids.
Delicious!

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half and line bottom of pan. Mix pudding just as it says on the box. Mix Cool Whip and pudding well. Spread on Twinkies. Break Heath bars on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chrissy's shepherd's pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with mashed potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until pie is hot through.
Add shredded cheese to top during last 5 minutes baking time and allow to melt.

title: hot chili bean and corn salad
directions: Combine beans, corn, celery and picante sauce.
Set out at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower until just tender.
Brown mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and gradually add milk and salt. Cook until thick.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/4 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add garlic cheese and mushroom soup. Add remaining ingredients and serve in chafing dish.

title: dirty rice recipe
directions: Saute gizzards first in enough cooking oil to cover bottom of pan until brown and tender.
Add water occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add onions.
Saute until done.
Add half of the bell pepper, finely chopped.
Saute.
Add water level with gizzards. Let simmer awhile, then add livers.
(Add flour to thicken, if necessary.)
Let simmer until livers and gizzards are done.
Turn off heat.
Add remaining bell pepper and green onions.
Stir in approximately 2 1/2 to 3 cups cooked rice.

title: sausage and pineapple
directions: Slice sausage crosswise into 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Brown sausage in skillet.
Add pineapple with juice and brown sugar. Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: homemade noodle dough
directions: In large bowl mix flour and salt.
Make a hole in center of flour and add eggs and oil.
Pour in water and stir until dough is stiff.
You may need to work in more flour depending on the size of your eggs.
Place dough on heavily floured surface and knead 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Cut dough in halves.
Roll out each half to desired thickness. Cut in strips.
Cook to desired tenderness.
Add plenty of butter and Parmesan cheese or your favorite sauce.

title: orange blossom cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package.
Fold in 1/3 cup ground orange.
Pour into 8 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Bake according to package.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients real good. Then add the other ingredients. Mix thoroughly. With 2 teaspoons, spoon out into hot canola oil.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, corn meal and flour lightly with a fork.
Add other ingredients.
Beat all with a mixer until smooth.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add this just before serving.
Serves 25 (8-ounce) cups.

title: never fail pie dough
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco and salt into crumbs.
Beat egg and vinegar.
Add cold water to equal 1/2 cup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Spray 3-quart round casserole with Pam.
Place sliced potatoes around edge of casserole.
Pour peas in center of potatoes.
Top with sliced onion.
Lay chicken on top and cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: biscuit tostadas
directions: In skillet, cook beef over medium heat until well done, drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups salsa and heat through.
Split each biscuit in half; flatten into 4-inch rounds on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with meat mixture, cheese, lettuce and remaining salsa.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken and Veg-All in dish.
Mix 1 1/2 cans broth with chicken and mushroom soup; pour over Veg-All and chicken.
Combine Bisquick and milk.
Pour over Veg-All and chicken.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over top and bake at 400° until brown (35 to 40 minutes).

title: frozen slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage and let stand for 1 hour.
Place cabbage in clean cheesecloth and squeeze out all of the water. Add to cabbage the grated carrot and grated green pepper.
Boil white vinegar, mustard seed, sugar and celery seed for 1 minute; pour over cabbage and let cool.
Fill plastic cartons such as oleo comes in; cover and freeze.
To serve, remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Stir and serve.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Combine half of the asparagus liquid and other ingredients in saucepan; stir well and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Pour over asparagus; chill 8 hours or overnight.
Yields 8 servings.

title: devil's island eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Add bacon and dressing; mix well.
Refill egg whites.
Garnish with pimento or parsley, if desired.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil, until sugar is dissolved.
Add frozen concentrates and brandy.
Mix and freeze.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage
and drain.
Beat eggs and milk.	Add the sausage, eggs
and milk to the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight in
a
greased baking dish.
Take out the next morning 30	minutes
before
baking.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.
Take cover off for the last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: christmas casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass pan (buttered), put croutons first, then cheese, then sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard; pour over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta salad a la zacher
directions: Cook rotini pasta per package directions.
Drain thoroughly. Set aside to cool.
Sprinkle one package dry salad dressing mix over pasta.
Cook frozen vegetables until thawed, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Add to pasta.
Cut in 1/2 the tomatoes and add to salad.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 of second package dry salad dressing mix over salad.
Add 1 bottle salad dressing over pasta salad.
Mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.
Add remaining bottled salad dressing to taste.

title: braunschweiger cheese ball
directions: Soften 8 ounces of cream cheese and braunschweiger one hour at room temperature in large mixing bowl.
Add dry onion soup mix and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix until well blended.
Form into a ball on paper plate and chill for 3 hours or until ball is firm. Soften 3 ounces cream cheese.

title: summer pudding
directions: You will also need 6 to 8 cup pudding mold or bowl with steep sides.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling; add Jell-O from package.
Cool. Blend with a fork the cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Mix well with pineapple and Jell-O mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and celery.
Stir in nuts.
Add a touch of green food coloring if you desire color.
This yields about 24 squares.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Oil loaf pan with olive oil and spray with Pam.
Mix all ingredients well; form into loaf.
Put into pan and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with baked potatoes, lettuce and tomato salad and string beans.

title: aunt minnie's date-nut bread
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl. Add the boiling water and set aside until cold.
Add the egg.
Measure the flour and sift with the soda and cream of tartar.
Add to mixture.
Last add the nuts and vanilla.
Fill pans half full and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender (may be microwaved on High for approximately 20 minutes).
Debone chicken; chop into smaller pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Stir in chicken.
In separate bowl, mix butter into stuffing.
Pat chicken mixture into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon buttered stuffing over this. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and dry jello. Mix well. Fold in oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add salt, flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix together, then add apples and nuts.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomato paste and 1 cup water; salt and pepper and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Heat milk and cream cheese in saucepan over medium heat.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and green pepper and noodles.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole, alternate layers of noodles and meat sauce.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top before serving.

title: good dessert
directions: Add 1 cup sugar gradually to egg whites.
Fold crackers and nuts
into egg whites.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch
baking
dish. Cool completely.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Coat pecan pieces in melted butter. Put coated pecans on cookie sheet and heat for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Melt almond bark and pour pecans in almond bark. Stir pecans until all pieces are coated. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Let sit until hard.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shakeable container, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic salt and pepper.
Place chicken in roasting pan and pour mixture over.
Cover and bake approximately 40 minutes. Uncover 10 minutes and bake longer.

title: low-fat mandarin blueberry muffins
directions: Combine the flour, oat bran, sugar and baking powder and stir to mix well.
Crush the orange segments slightly and add the oranges and their syrup, egg whites and vanilla extract to the flour mixture.
Stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in the blueberries.

title: hamburger skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add can of tomatoes, macaroni, salt, pepper, oregano and onion.
Cook until macaroni is tender and mixture should be somewhat dry.
Pour mixture in casserole dish and put grated cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: rosy cinnamon apples(microwave)
directions: Combine candies and water in 2-cup glass measure.
Microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring at 1 minute intervals until candy dissolves.
Place apples in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour melted candy mixture over the apples; cover and microwave at High for 7 to 9 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion flakes.
Split rolls in half horizontally and place bottom layers back in tinfoil pans.
Alternate layers of ham and layers of cheese.
Cover with top layer of rolls.
Make servings by cutting between rolls.
Drizzle mixture over rolls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or may be wrapped and frozen and cooked later. Great for party finger food or showers!

title: short-cut bacon water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon into 2-inch strips.
Wrap around water chestnuts and secure with toothpicks.
Microwave on High until bacon is cooked. Put in shallow pan and cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger-cabbage dinner
directions: Saute onion and pepper in melted oleo until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add ground chuck and cook until brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onion and pepper to browned beef.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Lightly grease a 10-inch square size Pyrex dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, broth, onion, salt and pepper.
Add the noodles and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef patties with mushrooms
directions: Mix together and press into patties on cookie sheet.
Put in fridge and cool for 3 hours.
Roll in flour.
Brown on both sides. Put in baking dish.
Add soup mixed with water.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and place a layer in the bottom of casserole. Mix the rest of the ingredients and place on top of layer of squash.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in greased casserole.
Cover for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: nutty broccoli-bac'n salad
directions: Stir yogurt; mix in vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli. Toss to combine.
Before serving, stir in Bac'n Chips and nuts.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar first, then add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Mix spices and flour together.
Add to oil mixture; stir in plums and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tiny wiener tid bits
directions: Simmer all together in crock-pot or bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: man's salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions and add pineapple.
Stir well and add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the soup.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
About 25 minutes before it's done, pour mushroom soup over the meat loaf.

title: cloud 9 biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Add egg with milk all at once, stirring only until barely mixed.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 18 to 20 times.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased pan close together if you don't want a lot of crust, or 3/4 inch apart if you want them crusty.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes

title: veg all and noodles
directions: Pour Veg All (juice and all) into 3-quart sauce pan.
Add water and noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Drain.
Add lots of butter.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, peppers, onions and cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Put on stove and bring to a boil.
Add chopped vegetables.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Seal while hot.

title: almond crescents
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and almonds.
Sift flour and salt together and work in.
Chill dough.
Roll with hands pencil thick.
Cut in 2 1/2-inch lengths.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes until set.
While warm, dip in 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: maryland crab imperial
directions: Remove cartilage and shells from crabmeat.

title: chocolate delight dessert
directions: Bake for 20 minutes at 325° (stirring while baking).
Cool before adding 2nd layer.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 2 eggs at a time and beat after each.
Add flour and salt gradually.
Mix soda in buttermilk and alternate with flour.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 275° in gas stove or 300° in electric stove.
Do not open oven.
Grease and flour pan well.

title: aunt lil's date nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak dates in hot water with soda, approximately 30 minutes.
Drain, set aside.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix as listed in order.
Beat after each ingredient.
Pour in well-greased pan (9 x 12-inch, or there about).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add sifted sugar.
Cream well. Blend in unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in pecans and cherries.
Chill 1 hour.
(To chill dough, place in freezer.)

title: waffles
directions: Mix the eggs, milk and oil in large bowl.
Blend flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cardamon together, then add to egg mixture.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, add sugar and egg yolks, beat. Combine flour and soda, add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: perfect divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt; stir until sugar dissolves.
Heat to boiling; cover and boil for 2 minutes. Uncover; cook to soft ball stage or 238°.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites, beating constantly, using electric mixer.

title: opal's pickles
directions: Drain and wash sour pickles; slice pickles and set aside.
Put the pickles in the gallon jar or another large container (such as a crock jar or even a large plastic container) and pour the sugar over the sliced pickles.
Gently mix; let pickles sit for about an hour stirring every 15 minutes; it will begin to liquify. After an hour, pour the remaining ingredients over the pickles; stir mixture and cover.
Leave at room temperature for 48 hours, stirring once or twice a day for two days.
When the sugar has dissolved put pickles in smaller jars and keep refrigerated.

title: nonfat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 9 x 5-inch with Pam.
Combine ingredients and blend at medium speed with mixer.
Pour into loaf pan and bake one hour until center is done.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix nuts and coconut; shake in pan to spread.
Mix cake mix according to directions; pour over nut mixture.
Melt oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and cover. Let it sit overnight to firm up. Roll into logs and cut into 1-inch sections. Wrap in decorative foil and papers. Yield: 48.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise with the ingredients.
Any of the ingredients may be omitted and others added as desired.
Serve cold with fish or cold meat dishes.
Makes 1 1/3 cups sauce.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Add egg to sugar, molasses and melted shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then add buttermilk.
Blend well and bake for approximately 40 minutes.

title: strawberry salsa
directions: Blend and serve with tortilla chips.

title: emily gayles fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices; sift and set aside.
In large bowl of mixer, beat at medium speed.
Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until well mixed.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Using electric mixer on slow speed, mix together flour, Crisco, baking powder and salt.
In separate measuring cup, mix together the egg and vinegar.
Add enough water to make 1 cup. Add to flour mixture; beat thoroughly.
Roll out dough as usual, using plenty of flour to roll, as this is very soft dough. Freezes very well.
Makes 6 pie crusts.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken in butter for 4 minutes per side; remove chicken and set aside.
Add Rice-A-Roni to skillet and cook, stirring, until golden.
Stir in tomatoes, water, Spanish seasoning mix and okra.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: potato carrot casserole
directions: Parboil potatoes and carrots.
Drain.
Saute chopped onion in fat.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir until well blended.
Slowly add milk while stirring until thick creamy sauce is formed.
Pour sauce over vegetables in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: chinese noodle cookies
directions: Melt bits and add peanut butter; beat until smooth.
Pour over noodles and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper and let set.

title: cream of cheese soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan or kettle, then stir in flour.
Stir constantly over medium heat, 1 minute, until thick and bubbly.
Add milk, ham and onion, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened.
Reduce heat to lowest setting. Stir in cheese and continue stirring until cheese is melted and soup is smooth.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter in a large bowl; mix together.
Cook sugar and Milnot together until it forms soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour entire mixture into peanut butter mixture; stir until creamy.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.
Candy cuts better if allowed to sit overnight.

title: tomato soup meat loaf
directions: Mix together meat, onion, pepper, egg, bread crumbs and 1/2 can tomato soup. Put in pan to bake. Poke 3 holes in loaf and spread Worcestershire. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out of oven and drain off the grease. Put rest of tomato soup on top and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread. Combine sausage, beef and bread. Saute onion in butter. Add meat along with mashed potatoes. Add all seasoning and eggs. Beat together with electric mixer until light. Shape into ball and brown in butter. Prepare gravy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Butter a Bundt pan and put pecans in the bottom.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add drained pineapple and strawberries.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot crab meat
directions: Break up crab meat.
Add all ingredients.
Put in covered dish and top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Should be bubbling.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: *Use any combination of chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, peanuts or granola chunks.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil over low heat.
Add onion, green peppers, celery and tomatoes.
Cover; cook gently about 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandmother's spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in heavy large pan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is translucent, about 4 minutes.
Add meat and cook until brown, about 8 minutes.
Drain; mix parsley, bay leaves and basil into meat and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, water, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer until reduced to sauce consistency, breaking up tomatoes with spoon. Takes about 2 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves.
Pour syrup over corn; mix well.
Grease hands with butter.
Shape popcorn mixture into balls.

title: boiled rice
directions: Do not wash rice before cooking.
Combine rice with water and salt in heavy 2 to 3-quart pan.
Bring water to hard boil, uncovered.
Lower heat, add oleo, cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Do not lift lid or stir.
And do not rinse after cooking.
Result:
Nice even fluffy rice.

title: tortillas for burritos
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Spoon 3 tablespoons batter onto a moderate hot ungreased griddle.
Spread batter with back of spoon to 6-inch very thin pancake.
Turn tortillas when edges begin to look dry.
Fill with your favorite chopped lettuce, grated cheese, chopped tomato, sour cream and etc.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Turn onto smooth surface and knead (it will be hot - be careful).
Add food coloring (to sectioned parts) of your choice.
Store in covered containers.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour. Measure and resift with sugar. Beat egg, add milk and shortening. Add flour mixture and beat until smooth. Fold in corn and let stand 5 to 10 minutes while you heat shortening for frying. Drop by tsp. into 360 degrees heated shortening.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Mix together, bake at 375 degrees for 6 - 8 minutes.

title: moondrop cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions for a round cake. Mix together sour cream, sugar and crushed pineapple with juice. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for icing.
Slice cake in half to make 4 layers.
Place 1 layer on plate.
Cover with pineapple mixture.
Continue this, then leave top layer uncovered.
Combine whipped topping with the cup of pineapple mixture; put on top and sides.
Cover cake and refrigerate.
This cake looks like a large snowball.

title: "join the party" salad
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise and 1 cup sour cream.
Layer lettuce, celery, carrots, onion, eggs, bacon, cheese and peas in large glass salad bowl.
Spread mayonnaise/sour cream mixture.
Top with small amount crumbled bacon, Cheddar cheese and sliced egg. Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: carnival cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease, then line with wax paper, the bottom of two 1 1/2 x 9-inch layer pans.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a bread loaf pan.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; beat until light.
Add mashed banana.
Stir in soft ingredients, beating smooth.
Add walnuts.
Pour into pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and line with tinfoil 2 medium or 3 small tins.
Cream 2/3 cup shortening, 2/3 cup sugar or 1/3 sugar substitute; add 4 eggs, 1 can pumpkin or 2 cups cooked pumpkin or squash and 2/3 cup water.
Mix and add 3 1/2 cups flour, 2 teaspoons soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon cloves, 1 cup raisins and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli.
Cut in small pieces.
Combine broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour dressing over broccoli.
Refrigerate 2 hours or more before serving.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring to a boil the water, sugar, cream of tartar and lemon juice.
Let boil 2 minutes and drop in Ritz crackers.
When crackers become very moist and are mixed with other ingredients into a nice consistency for pouring, put in a pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter, using about 1/2 stick.
Bake in 450° oven until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until just done. Drain. Whisk together next 4 ingredients and pour over macaroni in an ovenproof dish.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for 30 minutes to 1 hour until set.
Old fashioned and good!

title: karmel korn
directions: Put all ingredients in a large heavy saucepan (5-quart). Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until not quite soft ball stage (225° to 230°).
Pour over popped corn and stir to coat evenly.
This will stay soft if kept in airtight container.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in pie filling and smooth over bottom.
Dump in undrained pineapple and smooth but do not mix.
Dump in dry cake mix, then nuts, again only smoothing, not mixing after each addition.
Place butter pieces on top.
Bake for 1 hour or until lightly golden.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: chicken for a busy day
directions: Chop the onions.
Pare and quarter the potatoes and carrots. Place butter and oil in a frypan or Dutch oven, then turn heat to medium.
Add onions and cook until onions are soft, about 5 minutes.
Push onions aside and add chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon garlic powder and 1 teaspoon oregano and brown slightly for about 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over and sprinkle with remaining garlic powder and oregano.
Brown this side slightly for an additional 4 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and water.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place lid on and turn heat to high, just long enough until water starts to boil.
Turn heat to low and simmer for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Mix sour cream, soup, chicken and poppy seed together.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and place on top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: norma's cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage, peas, green onions and half of the peanuts together.
Mix the dressing and apply to salad several hours before serving (overnight is okay).
Garnish with the rest of the peanuts.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix the bread crumbs, cornmeal, curry powder and salt.
Coat chicken pieces.
Place in pan meaty side down.
Roll pieces of peeled potatoes and carrots in crumb mixture; place around chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes; turn and bake another 30 minutes.

title: indian pie
directions: Mix flour, Crisco,
baking
powder,
salt
and	raisins together.
Add water to make
dough.
Make	one
big piece and flatten dough to about 1-inch
thick
and
put in greased pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in shaker container.

title: banana split cake
directions: Apply a layer at a time.

title: mom's vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell
and
bake at about 350° until well browned, around 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, then syrup, salt, vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and cook approximately 60 minutes in preheated oven at 360°.
Crust should be light brown.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place skinned chicken in baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil the dressing, cranberry sauce and soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Seal with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes. Serve over rice.
Delicious!

title: apple crunch bars
directions: You will also need vegetable oil spray.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; shape into balls and put in skillet.
Cover with tomato juice to the top of balls.
Add celery salt and cloves.
Simmer 1 hour, covered.

title: layered cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch bake dish, melt margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order given.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then chill.
Cut into bars.

title: diabetic sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating well.
Let stand 5 minutes so that the oats will absorb moisture.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute on cookie sheet; transfer to wire rack to cool completely.

title: chili beans
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, onions, green pepper and celery until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain kidney beans.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ghoul-ade
directions: In a large pitcher, mix Kool-Aids together with sugar. Add water and mix well. Chill. Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Let partially set and beat until light and fluffy.
Add balance of ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese dip
directions: Dice up cheese and put on low heat in saucepan.
Add contents of Ro-Tel can to cheese.
Turn to medium heat and stir until all cheese is melted.
Careful not to scorch.
Serve with tortilla chips, Fritos or potato chips.
This is also great over Mexican dishes or with chili.

title: skippy bars
directions: Melt over low heat peanut butter and butter; remove from heat and stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to other ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with equal parts of butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar.

title: bundt cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, cooking oil and water in bowl; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Beat 8 minutes at highest speed; add vanilla and butter flavoring. Grease an angel food or Bundt pan.

title: colorful fruit bowl
directions: Combined first 4 ingredients and chill.
Peel and section oranges and grapefruit, add remaining fruit and toss gently. Place in individual serving bowls and using a slotted spoon, drizzle dressing over.
Serve immediately.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs and beat after each one. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add enough flour for stiff dough. Chill 2 hours.
Roll very thin (1/8-inch) on a floured surface. Cut out and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and egg brunch
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread crumbs and ham in dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Pour over cheese.
Pour butter over it all.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in order given.	It mixes better with hands
because the warmth of your hands makes the cheese blend better with
the
other
ingredients.
Form
into
small balls and press with	fork.
Bake
at 350° about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer container with refried beans. Mash the avocados with some mayonnaise. Layer on top of beans. Spread the sour cream on top of this and then spread the picante sauce on top of this. Sprinkle cheese on picante sauce. Add tomatoes, onions and olives. Keeps in refrigerator. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan.
Heat syrup, margarine and chips to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a bowl; toss until coated. Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press into pan with the buttered back of a spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut, then store at room temperature.

title: peppermint chiffon pie
directions: Soften the gelatine in the cold water; dissolve over hot water.
Add it to the stiffly beaten egg whites, which have been beaten with the flour.
Fold in the whipped cream and the candy, which has been thoroughly crushed with the salt and vanilla.
Turn this mixture into the chocolate cookie crust.

title: peanut butter-butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Add corn flakes and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper to cool and harden.

title: frozen salad
directions: Beat egg yolks with salt, sugar, juice of pineapple and lemon juice.
Heat until it thickens.
Remove from stove; add pineapple. Set aside to cool.
Then add stiffly beaten egg whites, then fold in whipped cream.
Put crumbs in bottom of glass pan, saving a few for the top.
Freeze and serve frozen.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic very fine; set aside. Salt, pepper and roll chicken in flour. Brown well in small amount of oil. Remove from pan; add onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic and parsley flakes. Saute until tender. Add tomatoes, mushrooms and Italian seasoning. Place chicken in large greased baking dish. Pour tomato mixture over chicken; sprinkle well with Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly with lid or tinfoil. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven; uncover and bake 15 minutes longer. Serve over cooked buttered noodles. Pass the Parmesan cheese!

title: hopi indian potato bread
directions: Flour
enough until you barely can
handle
and
grease dough. Let stand 10 minutes. Knead and grease.
Let rise until double size; knead and grease.
Let rise again until double in size, then roll to desired size.
(I usually make biscuits and freeze some.) Let dough rise double again and bake at 375° for about 35 to 45 minutes. You can grease or butter to soften the crust.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Pound on chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of butter and oil in large skillet; cook chicken over high heat on each side for 4 minutes.
After cooking, place chicken on a platter.
Add chives, lime juice, brandy, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook for 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth; stir until smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil. Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.
Can be served with noodles and tomato sauce.

title: capellini with chilled tomatoes, black olives and garlic
directions: Put chopped tomatoes in a strainer over a large bowl; place bowl in refrigerator and let tomatoes drain for at least 30 minutes.
Combine garlic, olives, chili pepper, oil, lime juice, cilantro, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate mixture.
Cook capellini in 3 quarts boiling, salted water; test after 3 minutes.
Cook until al dente.
While pasta is cooking, combine garlic mixture with drained tomatoes; discard juice.
Drain pasta and put in bowl; toss immediately with sauce.

title: s'more banana dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, baking mix and sugar; stir in margarine until moistened.

Press in bottom of glass dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Microwave, uncovered, on High, rotating 1/2 turn every minute, until crust bubbles up slightly and then begins to flatten, 1 1/2 to 3 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Add in layers as listed.
Use 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until browned well.

title: custard base for ice cream
directions: Combine cream, milk and sugar in a heavy saucepan or double boiler.
Heat until warm and sugar is completely dissolved.
Beat egg yolks until slightly creamy.
Add 1 cup cream mixture to the yolks while whisking lightly, mix thoroughly.
Continue to whisk, add remaining cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until back of spoon is thinly coated, about 8 minutes.
DO NOT allow mixture to boil or custard will curdle.
Cool and use in ice cream recipes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: tomato salad
directions: Peel, core and slice tomatoes.
Peel and slice onions.
Place tomatoes in dish.
Place onions over in rings.
Make dressing. Pour over tomatoes; let set 1 hour before serving.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Drain spinach, mix together cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Layer sauce, then noodles and repeat until all sauce and noodles are used.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top.
Pour the 1/4 c. of water around edge and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes and serve.

title: golden cheddar biscuits
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Mix dry ingredients together; add to shortening and sugar mixture. Blend in egg, milk and cheese. Divide mixture equally into a greased muffin (12 cup or two 6-cup) pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet-sour spareribs chinese style
directions: Cut spareribs in small pieces and brown in frying pan.
Add 1/2 cup of water, the raisins and salt.
Cover pan tightly and cook over very low heat for 20 minutes.
Add green peppers.

Stir in cornstarch blended with sugar, vinegar and 1 cup of water. Cover and continue cooking over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally and adding more water as needed to prevent drying. Before serving, add soy sauce to taste.

title: louisiana chicken-filled biscuit dumplings
directions: Chop chicken; place in mixing bowl.
Add celery, 2 tablespoons onion, parsley flakes and pepper; mix well.
Separate biscuits; pat or roll out each biscuit to a 4-inch circle.
Place a small amount of chicken mixture on each biscuit.
Wrap dough around mixture; press edges together firmly.
Combine soups, 1 1/4 cups water, green pepper and remaining onion in a 3-quart saucepan; heat until bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Place dumplings, sealed edges down, in soup mixture; spoon soup mixture over dumplings.
Cover tightly. Cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes, or until dumplings are cooked through.
Serve hot, using soup mixture as sauce.
Yields 10 dumplings.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, mix milk and pudding mix and beat.
Add pumpkin, spice and 2 cups Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour into crust. Chill for 4 hours.
Garnish with 2 cups Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place vegetables and crackers in a large bowl.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs, salt, pepper, oregano, oil and wine.
Add egg mixture to vegetables.
Toss to blend. Pour into greased 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 55 minutes.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Take garlic salt, onion salt and paprika and mix into sour cream. Cut chicken into strips. Crumble potato chips. Dip chicken in sour cream mixture and roll in potato chip crumbs. Place chicken in baking dish. Pour melted butter over chicken and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat the egg and mix with all the other ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese sauce(this works well in a double boiler.)
directions: Melt margarine. Stir in flour and salt. Add milk and stir until thickens. Add cheese; stir until melted. This sauce can be used on baked potatoes, horseshoes, tortilla chips, etc.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over walnuts coated with egg white and water.
Mix until well coated.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes. Cool and separate.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar. Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.
Pour in a dish and freeze.
Set out 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Will keep 4 to 6 weeks.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Cube bread; put in bottom of casserole.
Combine cheese, margarine and meat; sprinkle over bread cubes.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Add over top of the other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dumplings(these dumplings will melt in your mouth.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Roll out thin on slightly floured surface and cut into thin strips.
Let dry 2 hours or longer.

title: diane fritts' wonderful white cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate adding milk and flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla extract and mix well.
Bake at 350°. Makes 40 cupcakes.

title: chicken roulade a la hart
directions: Saute onions, peppers and seasoning for a minute or so.
Mix with sausage, chopped tomatoes, garlic, salt and pepper.
Beat chicken breast until real thin.
Cover breast with filling; fold in the sides and roll in flour and egg with bread crumbs.
Deep fry for a few minutes to seal, then bake in oven at 300° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, depending on oven.
Bon appetit!

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9-inch pan and line with 2/3 cookie crumbs.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs and pour into pan. Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 20 minutes.
Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheese cake.
Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Cook for 5 minutes at 475°.

title: candied apples
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt desired amount of candy coating, stirring frequently.
With fork, dip pretzels, cherries with stems, large fresh strawberries or other fruit into warm candy coating*; let excess coating drip off.
Place on aluminum foil or wax paper-lined baking sheet.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin (or squash) bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add all other ingredients.
Grease and flour loaf tin.
Pour mixture into loaf tin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box and cool.
Punch holes in top of cake (with fork).
Pour ice cream toppings over cake.
Top with Cool Whip, pecans and Heath bar bits.
Refrigerate.

title: southwest taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
Partially bake pie crust for 10 minutes; cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
In a small mixing bowl, combine refried beans and 1/2 cup taco sauce.

title: lemon refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and then eggs and extract.
Sift dry ingredients and add a little at a time to creamed mixture. Form into long rolls.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Slice; press pecan half in middle.
Cook at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken pieces until browned on all sides.
With slotted spoon, remove pieces to large bowl.
In drippings remaining in skillet over medium heat, cook green peppers and onion until tender-crisp, stirring frequently.
Return chicken pieces to skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and salt.
Drain juice from pineapple chunks into skillet; reserve chunks.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Stir in pineapple chunks.
In cup, stir water and cornstarch until blended.
Gradually stir cornstarch mixture into simmering liquid in skillet.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly until mixture is slightly thickened.
Makes 5 servings, 500 calories per serving.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Mix potatoes, cream cheese, egg and salt together until creamy. Add onion and pimentos.
Put in ungreased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Double for company.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: creamsickle jello mold frozen
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water and add 4 ice cubes. Chop up vanilla ice cream and fold into Jell-O.
Place into mold and place in freezer.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut biscuits into fourths. Sprinkle onion powder, garlic powder and cheese over butter.
Roll biscuits in butter.
Bake about 9 minutes at 400° or until light brown.

title: pigs-in-blanket ala roma(sicilian style)
directions: The only ingredient I have changed is to sometimes use seasoned salt instead of the regular table salt.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Mix all ingredients well, EXCEPT CHOCOLATE CHIPS AND WALNUTS. Mix for 3 to 4 minutes. Fold in chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar after turning out of pan and a bit cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press in pan.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: oyster sauce
directions: Make a white sauce with the milk and part of the butter, quite thick.
Cream egg yolks with remainder of butter; add mustard mixed with lemon juice.
Add egg whites, chopped fine.
Mix with white sauce.
Cook oysters separately just until the edges curl.
Mix all together.
Season to taste.
Stir a lot, it can stick.

title: down south barbecue
directions: Put 1/2 of the onions in the bottom of a crock-pot.
Add the meat and the other ingredients (except barbecue sauce) with the remaining onion on top.
Cover and cook overnight or 8 to 12 hours on low.
Remove bone, fat and liquid.
Add barbecue sauce and mix well.
Cook on low for an additional 3 to 5 hours.
Serve from crock-pot on large buns.

title: avila bean field surprise(or bean and cheese dip)
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with a mixer.
Layer bottom of a 1 3/4-quart baking dish with half of the bean mixture.
Sprinkle half of grated cheeses over beans.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut up cooked turkey.
Chop celery and onions.
Mix together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and soup. Add turkey, onions, celery, croutons and almonds; mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and dry pudding mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Fold in drained fruit. Chill 30 minutes before serving.
You may substitute any fruit for fruit cocktail, if you prefer.
This recipe is sugar-free and fat-free.

title: ham rolls
directions: Remove rolls from tin pan and cut them in half.
Place bottom half of rolls back in pan.
Mix together onions, mustard, poppy seed, butter, salt and pepper.
Spread this mixture on bottom half of rolls.
Now put top half of rolls back on.
Cover with foil. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: cherry oatmeal dreams
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine with oatmeal. Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, cherry liquid and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, cherries and nuts. Shape into small balls.
Coat with oats and nuts.
Top each with a cherry half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: glazed carrots with apples
directions: Combine ingredients in 1-quart casserole. Cover with plastic wrap or lid.
Microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on High.
Stir. Microwave again for 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate; stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2
minutes or until dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thick.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: baked surprise fudge pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan. Blend cocoa, 1/4 teaspoon salt and brown sugar together and sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over top of batter. Do not blend.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes so sauce is on top.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mixture will be soft. Shape into walnut size balls. Place in single layer in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: cantaloupe cooler
directions: Cut cantaloupes into wedges.
Cut the peel away from the flesh and cut melons into chunks.
Put chunks in blender with orange juice; blend until smooth.
Add a jigger of rum if you like.

title: easy corn fixin's
directions: Drain corn from can.
Place bacon in a 1-pint saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Add seasoning salt.
Bring to boil for 15 minutes.
Turn temperature down to low. Add corn and sugar, stir and mix well.
Add margarine, cover and serve promptly from stove. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon vegetable salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water; let cool.
Add all other ingredients to jello mixture.
Pour in molds or large casserole dish.
Refrigerate until jello is set.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add seasoning.
Mix according to directions.
Add to other ingredients.
Top with dressing and refrigerate.

title: hamburger supper
directions: Brown meat until done.
Put meat into casserole dish.
Add tomato soup, corn and noodles.
Grate cheese; add.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Brown seasoned chicken 4 minutes on each side or until cooked.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Heat oil and saute onions and peppers until onions are soft.
Add tomato sauce, water and other ingredients, except rice and peas. Stir well; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
While this cooks, tear chicken in pieces.
Add chicken, rice and peas.
Heat until warm through.

title: carolina peach cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil and mix well.
Add eggs, mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt, mix well.
Add flour mixture to mixture in large bowl, mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 325 degree oven 45 to 50 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients. Spread over pineapple.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle margarine over cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: drop scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat egg and egg yolk.
Add milk.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, 1/4 cup sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add butter bits.
Mix this until it resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins and pecans; stir until evenly distributed. Form a well in center and then pour in egg mixture.
Quickly stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Use fork, don't overstir. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet lightly dusted with flour. Place drops of batter, 1 to 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes. These may be served hot or rewarmed.
Suppose to be served with cottage cheese.
(I use topping and strawberry jam.)

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix chuck, egg, soup, monosodium glutamate and bread crumbs. Form into small balls.
Saute.
You may refrigerate until 30 minutes before serving.
In an electric skillet at medium heat, stir barbecue sauce and jelly.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, lemon juice and water.
Cook until thick; chill.
Bake crust and cool.
Mix chilled berries and sauce.
Pour into crust and top with whipped cream.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice to whipped cream.

title: sherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double berry punch
directions: Place chilled cranberry juice cocktail in a punch bowl. Slowly pour in carbonated beverage.
Top with raspberries.
Stir gently with an up-and-down motion to mix.
Serve over scoops of sherbet.
Yields 24 (4-ounce) servings.

title: pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl combine the potatoes, half of the cheese and half of the onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading the mixture across the bottom and up the sides of the pan forming a shell.

title: shrimp scampi with fresh herbs
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
In large pan over moderate heat, saute shrimp in olive oil.
Deglaze pan with white wine.
Add garlic and lemon juice.
Reduce liquid to half.
Add herbs.
Add cold butter over low heat to complete sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over linguini.
Serves 8.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and margarine in bowl; mix well. Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pie will make its own crust.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Oleo should be sliced to soften it.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan with oleo and sprinkle with sugar.
Combine all ingredients in blender and put on mix for 1 minute.
Pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Mix soups in baking pan (13 x 9-inches).
Use empty soup can to measure 1 can of wine and 1 can of rice.
Add to soups.
Lay chicken on top.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and stir. Bake 1 more hour.

title: old south barbecue sauce and chicken
directions: In oblong baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side up.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir sauce before serving.

title: french toast
directions: Butter 9 x 13 baking dish; arrange bread. Beat eggs, milk, cream, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour over bread. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: make-ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage, cook until brown and drain well.
Spread bread pieces in buttered dish (break bread in pieces); top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: potato salad 1
directions: After you cook the potatoes let them cool.
Then add all of the ingredients to the potatoes.
Just use 1/2 of the pickle relish.
Dice the tomatoes.
Put salt and pepper and red pepper to taste.

title: pizza, make two
directions: Mix well the warm water, salt, oil and yeast.
Place the flour in a large bowl.
Mix water, salt, oil and yeast in the flour. Knead real well for about 10 minutes.
Cut in two gobs and let it rise for 2 hours.
Grease bottoms of two 9-inch pizza pans with oil.
Place dough on pans and flatten down.
Put over Mozzarella cheese sauces and spread over 1/2 can of tomato sauce or more if you like.
