Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain the pork and beans and kidney beans; cook lima beans according to directions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Place in a large baking dish.
Cover with bacon and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jelly pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour and add to eggs.
Stir in melted butter and jelly.
Mix well. Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° until set.

title: apple ambrosia (microwave)
directions: Place applies in greased 8-inch square dish.
Pour orange juice over top.
Blend margarine and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients, and mix until crumbly.
Spread evenly over apples. Place in microwave oven and cook 9-11 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.
Use additional time if apples aren't fresh. Serve warm or cold, with cream if desired.

title: sauce mayonnaise
directions: Place egg yolks into warm bowl and whisk vigorously until thick.
Add teaspoon lemon juice along with teaspoon of mustard. Add 1/2 teaspoon of the oil at a time, whisking constantly.
You can whisk in 2 tablespoons of boiling water gradually to make it creamier.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bread dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Serve dip in a hollowed out round rye or pumpernickel bread with chunks of bread for dipping.

title: hot fruit bake
directions: Layer fruit in a large, flat Pyrex dish.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, cornstarch and juice from pineapple.
Cook over medium heat in a saucepan until mix is smooth and thickened.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes ahead.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine all other ingredients in a large pot.
Peel onions and put in sauce whole.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apple crumble
directions: Pour can of apples into greased pan.
Mix Bisquick, egg and sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle this mixture over apples.
Pour melted butter over the top of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Mix butter in milk.
Add lukewarm water and lemon rind and juice to milk mixture.
Set aside.

title: cranberry glaze and dipping sauce
directions: Mix together and cook for at least 5 minutes, longer is better.
Spread over scored ham.
Return ham to oven for at least 15 minutes.
Serve remaining sauce over ham slices.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese with melted butter and spinach.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole; cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into balls (walnut-sized) and press down slightly.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes. Can be frozen and heated before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash, dry and chop broccoli.
Boil eggs and chop.
To this add chopped onion, olives and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill several hours before serving.

title: *simple peanut butter cookies*
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients together.
Drop by 1/2 to 1 teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press fork into top.
Bake until light brown.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces suitable for serving.
Beat egg and salt together in a large bowl.
Add chicken and stir until all parts have been covered with egg mixture.
Then roll each separate piece of chicken in bread crumbs. Crushed bran flakes may be substituted for bread crumbs.
Place in well-buttered 2-quart casserole. Dot with bits of butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: heaven by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed.
Make mousse as directed.
When brownies are cool, break into pieces (small).
Cut up Skor bars. Layer brownies, mousse, candy, repeat and top with Cool Whip right before serving.

title: crock-pot caramel nut roll
directions: Turn slow cooker to high while preparing rolls.
Mix brown sugar and nuts together.
Dip each roll in melted butter and then in brown sugar mixture.
Place in well greased 2 pound coffee can or vented cake pan for slow cooker.
Sprinkle each layer with cinnamon.

title: caramel nut slices
directions: Mix ingredients
well;
form
into
2 rolls, 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap
in
waxed paper and chill.
Heat oven to 400°. Cut slices 1/8 inches thick.
Place a little apart on ungreased baking sheet;
bake
to
10 minutes until set, but not hard. Makes 6 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and the vanilla or lemon extract.
Gradually add the sugar and cream well.
Add the beaten eggs; then add the sifted flour.
Roll out thinly on a lightly floured board; sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Cut with a cookie cutter and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth with soup in 2 quart mixing bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 325° in oven for 40 minutes.

title: texas pralines
directions: Cut sheet of foil 2 feet long and spread on counter. In a 6-quart Dutch oven, combine sugar, milk and soda. Cook over medium heat.
Allow mixture to boil and turn brown.
Stir slightly around sides of pan.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Saute tomatoes and onion.
Add chili peppers. Mix all together.
Serve warm.

title: sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Cook sausage in skillet, breaking up meat with fork until browned.
Drain off fat.
Cool.
Put into large bowl when cooled. Add cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Mix with fork until blended. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until puffed and brown.
Can be frozen.
To reheat, bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all beans, mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with bacon and sliced onion rings.

title: hungarian cheese sticks
directions: Combine cottage cheese, butter and flour into a smooth dough. Refrigerate 8 hours.
Divide dough into 3 to 4 pieces.
Roll each piece out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into sticks about 1/2-inch wide by 2 1/2-inches long.
Put onto ungreased baking sheets. Brush tops with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with generous coating of grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in chunky peanut butter, vanilla and quick oats. Mix well and drop from teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand until hard.

title: relish plate for 100
directions: Make small
trays and add to, to keep neat and appetizing. Need 2 quarts dip.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour into sugar and crackers.
Put in layers in casserole dish.
First put layers of potatoes, then crumb mixture, ending with the crumb mixture on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 people.

title: mary's baked potatoes
directions: Grease baking medium dish with 1/2 stick butter.
Slice potatoes into pieces.
Chop up onions.
Lay on top.
Salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice and onion in hot Crisco.
Add juice from tomatoes and water to equal 2 cups liquid.
Chop tomatoes.
Add to rice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Use bought chocolate or graham cracker crust.
Do not bake. Mix ingredients with mixer.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate overnight.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Quarter and boil potatoes (as many as you need) for approximately 20 minutes.
After cooked, put in a bowl.
Pour approximately 1/4 to 1/2 bottle Italian dressing (I use Kraft fat-free dressing) over potatoes. Salt and pepper as desired. Serve warm.

title: corn and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together in glass bowl and bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour or until macaroni is done.

title: yugoslavian pecan crescents
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in egg yolks and sour cream; mix well. Gather in ball.
On lightly floured surface knead until smooth, 8 to 10 minutes.
Divide in thirds.

title: tangy little meatballs
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Combine with soup mix, eggs and liquids; let stand about 10 minutes.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 36 to 42 little balls.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add half of the meatballs and brown on all sides.
Remove and keep warm. Repeat with other half of meatballs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove skin and bone.
Cut chicken up to suit yourself.
Combine with other ingredients; put in a baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven, uncovered.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt, butter or margarine, lemon juice and grated rind.
Beat egg yolks and milk together; add to first mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into all.
Put into baking dish that can be placed into pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crabmeat or shrimp nippies
directions: Flake crabmeat and toss with mayonnaise and onions.
Spoon onto canape bases. Sprinkle generously with cheese. Broil 3 inches from source of heat, 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted and slightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Add oregano.
Melt cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Add meat to cheese.
Spread meat-cheese mixture on rye bread.
Heat in oven at 300° until hot.

title: michigan coleslaw
directions: In medium bowl, gently combine cabbage, celery, apples and raisins.
Add salad dressing and salt; toss lightly.
Put in pretty dish.

title: nora's molasses cake
directions: Mix molasses, sugar and vanilla together.
Add shortening and stir.
Add soda to warm water and stir in mixture.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 350 degrees until middle springs back to touch.

title: all bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over cereal and cool.
Set aside.
Add buttermilk to sugar, beat in eggs and oil.
Add to cooled cereals. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and combine mixtures. Bake as many as desired (fill muffin tins 2/3 full).
Refrigerate (will keep 4 to 6 weeks).
When you use batter that has been refrigerated, do not stir batter, just dip out to fill muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pink stuff
directions: Prepare
Dream	Whip
according
to package directions, using all milk
in place of water and milk called for.
Gently stir in mashed berries, pineapple, nuts and mayonnaise.
Whip cream.
Fold into mixture along with food coloring.
Put into 9 x 9
x	2-inch pan.
Freeze.
Top each serving with walnuts. Makes 8 to
10 servings.
Can
be	used
as salad or dessert. Serve slightly thawed.

title: potatoes victoria
directions: Bake potatoes at 375°.
Take out of oven and cut in halves. Place filling in bowls.
Mix in cream cheese, mayonnaise and a dash of Worcestershire sauce and whip with a mixer.
Put back into the empty potato shells.
Place back in oven and bake until crispy on top.
Top with cheese.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve fat. Combine reserved fat from bacon with sugar, salt, celery seed and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Combine potatoes, bacon, onions and eggs in a large bowl, tossing thoroughly.
Pour vinegar-fat mixture over top and toss lightly until potatoes are completely coated.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into cool water.
Place oil into large frying pan.
Heat butter.
Add potatoes and fry.
Add brown sugar. When potatoes are half fried, finish cooking until tender.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Trim bread crusts and discard.

Cut bread into 1-inch cubes. Place cubes in a single layer on a baking sheet. Coat the cubes with cooking spray; sprinkle with garlic powder. Toss well. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Set aside. Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Place over medium-high heat until hot. Add the chicken breasts and cook for 6 minutes on each side or until well done. Remove the chicken; cool and slice across the grain into thin slices; set aside. Combine lemon juice and the next 5 ingredients in a blender. Cover and process until smooth. Add 1/2 cup of the lemon juice mixture to the chicken; toss gently to coat.

title: striped bass or blue fish filets
directions: Arrange the two fillets on a lightly oiled baking pan.
Spread the chopped tomatoes evenly over the fillets.
Scatter the garlic slices over the tomatoes.
Sprinkle on the oregano, basil, parmesan cheese and hot pepper.
Dribble on the olive oil and season with salt.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 20 - 30 minutes or until the flesh of the fish flakes easily and the tomato topping is bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients, except nutmeg.
Pour in pie shell, sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 400° until knife
inserted comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Boil shells until soft.
Brown meat.
Use both or 1 of your choices of meat.
Add whole tomatoes, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic to meat (spices to taste).
Grate cheese; drain shells. Sprinkle some cheese on meat.
Take each shell and stuff with meat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
After stuffing all the shells, if any meat left, pour over shells.
Place stuffed shells in a baking dish.
(May stack on top of each other.)
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce on bottom of baking dish; add shells, then cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Cover dish to keep from drying out.
Each ingredient is to the individual's taste.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix well. Add 7-Up last.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese until melted.
Cook noodles.
Grind up ham.
In a casserole dish, put layer of noodles, then ham, then sauce.
Repeat layers, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin fluff(diet)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a glass baking dish sprayed with Pam coating.
Place in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn down oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes until done.
Cool pumpkin dish.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and heat; do not boil.
Make a syrup.
Pour over popcorn mix.
Stir in peanuts and M&M's.
Press into angel food cake pan.
Let set for 15 hours before removing from pan.
Slice and enjoy.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Place in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until topping is browned and rhubarb is tender, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in glass dish and heat for 2 minutes in microwave on defrost.
Turn dish and heat 1 minute more.
Drain off water, add onions and mix.
Cover and cook 3 minutes on high.
Stir after each minute.
Add soup and stir until blended.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add rice, cheese and salt, stir to blend.
Cook 1-2 minutes more.
Cover and let steam for 3-5 minutes.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place the ground beef in the bottom of a greased 9-inch cake pan.
Pour the juice off the green beans and spread the beans over the top of the beef.
Spread the mushroom soup over the beans, then top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Set aside four whole berries for garnish.
Slice remaining strawberries and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine cornstarch and water until smooth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat; stir in gelatin and sugar until dissolved.
Stir in sliced strawberries.
Pour into the crust.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Cut reserved strawberries in half.
Garnish each serving with whipped topping and a berry half.

title: snappy gazpacho
directions: Chop all the vegetables in food processor until of consistency you like.
Combine with the other ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly, at least 4 hours if possible.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days.

title: frosty freeze pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add sherbet; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with dollops of Cool Whip and maraschino cherries.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased pan.
Cook in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peach-apricot preserves
directions: Boil peaches, pineapple and sugar slowly for 15 minutes. Remove from heat
and stir in until thoroughly dissolved the jello.
Pour into jars or freezer containers and let stand overnight.
Freeze.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in broth gradually.
When sauce is done, stir in onion (or powder) and set aside, covered.
Cook noodles.
Drain and put in greased large casserole.
Add chicken, cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato cakes
directions: Cook potatoes almost done, and then grate.
Combine with egg, flour and enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Add onion and seasonings; form into cakes.
Using frying pan, cook in hot fat until golden brown and crisp.

title: colombian fresh banana cake(with seafoam frosting)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine mix, baking soda and eggs. Measure Coca-Cola.
Stir briskly until foaming stops and add to batter.
Blend ingredients just until moistened, then beat at high speed of electric mixer for 3 minutes, scraping bowl often. Combine mashed bananas with lemon juice.
Add to cake batter with nuts.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed and turn into a generously greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and turn right side upon rack to finish cooling.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes in small cubes.
Mince garlic.
Chop green onions and red onion.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes with liquid and all chopped jalapenos, salt, garlic salt and 1/8 cup lemon juice. Chill and serve with chips or beans.

title: toll house cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients with vanilla and water.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° (overbakes easily).

title: orange kiwi salsa
directions: Peel and section 2 oranges; halve orange sections.
Squeeze juice from remaining orange into medium sized bowl; add orange sections and remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or up to 2 days.
Serve with grilled chicken, duck, pork, lamb or fish.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: maple cream coffee treat
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In ungreased 9 x 13 pan, combine brown sugar, nuts, syrup and melted butter. Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth. Separate biscuits and press each into 4-inch circles. Spoon 1 tablespoon cream cheese in center and fold over forming finger shaped rolls. Place in pan seam side down on top of syrup mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool 3 minutes. Invert over serving platter. Be careful. Syrup mixture will be hot! Can be made the night ahead and baked the next day.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar; mix thoroughly.
Stir in unbeaten egg, egg yolk and vanilla.
Add gradually, dry ingredients and
chopped nuts; mix well.
Spread batter in a well-greased (bottom only) 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water and bouillon until soft.
Make a white sauce from the remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over broccoli and simmer 1/2 hour.
Put some cheese on, as much as you want.

title: crystallized nuts
directions: Heat 2 1/2 cups nuts in moderate oven (375°) for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Butter sides of heavy 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook without stirring to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat, beat by hand 1 minute or until mixture just begins to get creamy.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla and the nuts.
Stir gently until nuts are well coated and mixture becomes creamy.
Turn out on buttered platter or cookie sheet.
Separate at once, using 2 spoons or forks.
Makes about 1 pound of nuts.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In large bowl, cream the shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Make layers in a 9 x 9 baking dish of crackers, chicken, eggs, celery, and onions.
Dissolve soup in 1/2 c. chicken broth.
Add the remaining broth and pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: kugelis(lithuanian potato bake)
directions: Grate potatoes into a large bowl and cover with water.
Cut up the bacon into small pieces and fry, but not too crisp.
Remove from pan and saute the onion in the bacon drippings.
Remove from heat.
Drain the water off the potatoes.
Beat the eggs and add to the potatoes along with the bacon mixture, milk, salt and pepper and enough of the bread crumbs to form a mushy mixture.
Grease a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Pour entire mixture into pan and bake at 375° for half an hour.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for another hour.
It will be brown in color.
Serve with sour cream or applesauce.
It may also be eaten cold.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and dry the leaf lettuce.
Clean green onions and chop up (leafy parts included).
Cut lettuce.
Add onions to lettuce in a bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on a paper towel and crumble into bits.
Add vinegar, water and sugar to fat in pan.
Heat to boiling.
Add bacon to lettuce and onions.
Pour hot dressing over the lettuce.
Toss to mix and wilt the lettuce.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, flour and milk.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Chop celery, onion, green pepper and olives.
Quarter tomatoes, salami and pepperoni. Reserve tomatoes and cheese if you are not serving immediately. Mix oregano, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar separately.
Mix other ingredients, then pour oil and vinegar over.
Chill and serve.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add Miracle Whip, water and vanilla. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This is a great cake for those who cannot eat eggs.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, pecans and flour.
Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar; spread on crust.
Next, spread blueberry pie filling over this.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: avocado grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Onto 1 slice of bread, arrange cheese, tomato, avocado and sprouts; top with remaining slice of bread.
Spray small nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; set sandwich in skillet, cover and cook over medium-low heat until bottom is lightly browned, about 3 minutes.
Carefully turn sandwich over and cook until other side is lightly browned and cheese is melted, about 3 minutes longer.
Makes 1 serving.

title: three bean casserole
directions: In skillet, fry onion and bacon until brown.
At the same time, fry the ground beef in another skillet until brown.
Drain off excess fat and add to onion and bacon mixture.
In a small bowl, mix ketchup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, mustard and ginger.
In another bowl, combine all the beans.
Grease a large casserole and spread a thin layer of meat mixture over the bottom. Cover with a layer of beans, then sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes a large casserole .... and freezes well.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Line bottom of a loaf pan with wax paper that is well greased. Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix in cranberries and nuts.
Beat eggs slightly; add it to cranberry mixture with melted butter, vanilla, milk or orange juice.
Stir just enough that all dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stores and freezes well.

title: butterscotch pecan or walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs.
Add syrup, salt, vanilla, brown sugar and oleo.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes more.
(Until knife inserted in center comes out clean.)
Cool completely.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine all ingredients and press into greased casserole dish. Cover with foil. Bake for 2 hours. DO NOT PEEK. Serve with a salad and dinner rolls to complete your meal.

title: rice cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Add flour to thicken. Make into cakes and fry like hamburgers.

title: spoon bread
directions: In a saucepan, scald the milk, stir in corn meal.
Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, sugar, salt and baking powder.
In small bowl beat egg yolks.
Stir small amount of the hot mixture into egg yolks. Return all to pan and mix well.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold egg whites into hot mixture until well blended.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with a spoon. 6 servings.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix until blended.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Combine the milk, soups, pepper and onion.
Grease casserole dish.
Start casserole with a layer of noodles, then chicken and soup.
Repeat.
Top with cornflake crumbs; add small dabs of butter on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix together lightly first 3 ingredients.
Put 1/2 of mixture in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine chicken, onions, mayonnaise and salt; put over layer of stuffing mix already in pan.
Put the remaining half of stuffing mix on top of this.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over top of casserole.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: grape frost
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender and blend.
Pour into a glass.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine potatoes and 1/2 cup water.
Cook, covered, in the microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes or until very tender. Drain and mash potatoes with mixer.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, 1 tablespoon margarine, onion and salt and pepper.
Gradually beat in enough milk to make smooth and fluffy.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk.
Cook until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Add dates.
Cook until partially dissolved.
Remove from fire and beat.
Add nuts.
Cool a little.
Pour onto foil and shape into roll.
Cool then slice.

title: peach crumble cake
directions: Pour peaches and syrup into 9 x 13 pan. Arrange peaches so they are evenly distributed. Sprinkle entire package of cake mix over peaches. Drizzle melted butter over cake mix. In a separate bowl, mix sugar, coconut and nuts. Sprinkle over butter and cake mix. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chunky potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Boil until tender.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
After cooled, skin and cube potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place into serving dish and refrigerate.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Line pie crust with pecans.
Mix flour and sugar. Add syrup and beaten eggs. Add melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal drops
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; add milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Add oatmeal and flour.
Lightly dust nut meats with flour and add to oatmeal mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and onions in a large skillet until almost brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 25 minutes, then blend in one cup of sour cream.
Simmer 5 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
In a 12-inch skillet, brown chicken in oil, turning to brown evenly.
Remove chicken; add uncooked rice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until rice is light brown; stir in chicken broth, beer, cumin, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt, saffron and pepper.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture; season lightly with salt and pepper (to taste); bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender.

title: dump salad
directions: You will need 1 large Ziploc bag and 1 large clean flowerpot for this recipe.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat with a mixer for just a minute. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn down to 350° and cook for 40 or 45 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Note: The directions are for microwave cooking.

title: chili dip
directions: Mash chili beans.
Add to chili, cheese soup, Worcestershire sauce and chilies.
Heat until bubbling.
Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Cover with pecans.
Put margarine chunks over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, Spanish rice and egg together.
Shape into loaf or put in loaf pan.
Bake a 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
May be topped with catsup for baking.

title: no-bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk. Boil for 1 minute.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo until clear and cooked.
Separately cook spinach according to box directions. Squeeze and drain excess water.
Add soup and cheese to sauteed vegetables.
Stir until melted.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add spinach and bread crumbs and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in casserole dish.
Sprinkle additional bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: cottage cheese "sour cream"
directions: Put in blender.
Blend together at high speed until smooth and creamy.
Use as a dip on baked potatoes or as a substitute in many recipes that call for sour cream.

title: ground venison jerky
directions: Mix well.
Roll mixture between 2 sheets of wax paper with rolling pin to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in strips about 1 1/2-inch wide.
Put in dehydrater for 12 to 15 hours or oven at 150° on rack for 10 to 11 hours.
Store in paper bag or tin coffee can.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add wafers, coconut and pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured bundt pan or miniature loaf pans at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fritzie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Mix other ingredients in order given.
Form balls; roll in sugar.
Flatten lightly.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes until light brown.

title: october salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients. Combine the remaining ingredients and spread or spoon on top of the first mixture.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, salt and egg together; add chocolate chips and set aside.

title: italian noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain. Add cucumber, onion and tomato. Pour salad dressing over and stir all together.

title: almond cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have ungreased cookie sheets ready.

title: fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
In a large saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Add corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Add a few drops of red food coloring for a richer looking salad, if desired.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Stir until smooth and spread over marshmallows.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add rice and soups (undiluted).
Pour in greased casserole.
Top with crushed cornflakes or seasoned bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with a prepared cream cheese icing.

title: creamy italian risotto
directions: In an 8 to 10 inch frying pan, cook butter and onion over medium heat, stirring, until onion is translucent.
Add grain and stir until opaque about 2 minutes.
Add broth and bring to a boil over high heat, reduce heat to simmer uncovered.
Stir occasionally at first; then as liquid is almost aabsorbed, stir frequently until grain is tender to bite.
(Approximate cooking times for each grain follows.)
Add more liquid as needed, 1/4 cup at a time, to prevent sticking.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour batter into greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine salad dressing, onion, sugar, relish and mustard.
Blend well.
Stir in cooked macaroni, peas and eggs.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: grandmother's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add dry ingredients and sift twice.
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk.	Roll out on floured board to 3/4-inch.	Cut with biscuit cutter; place on greased pan. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in an iron skillet, add coconut and pecans. Cook slow until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in whip topping.
Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 cup caramel. Sprinkle 1/4 coconut mixture.
Make second layer in same way. Makes 2 pies.
Cover and place in freezer.
These frozen pies make a great Christmas gift.

title: pauline's creamed eggs
directions: Mix margarine and flour in pan until melted and smooth; no lumps.
Add milk and stir continually over heat until thickened. Add Coffee-mate, mixing well. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve over buttered toast.

title: mini blueberry muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease (4) loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
In a glass bowl, mix 3/4 cup of milk, all the buttermilk, 1 cup flour, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast.
In a large mixing bowl, place the remaining ingredients, except for nuts and cherries; mix well.
Add the milk mixture to the bowl and mix well. Fold in the nuts and cherries.
Divide the dough amongst the pans, bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: refrigerator dills
directions: Mix and refrigerate cold water, vinegar and salt.
Wash cucumbers and cut into spears.
Pack in sterilized jars, adding a sprig of dill, clove of garlic and small red pepper.
Pour liquid mixture over cucumbers and seal.
Store in refrigerator.
They will be ready in 7 to 10 days and will keep 3 months or longer.

title: wontons
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in the center of each wonton skin.
Fold wonton skin over filling to form triangle. Seal with water.
Deep fry wontons at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until brown and crispy. Drain on paper towels and serve with sauce.

title: lilla's sonora style chicken
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from oil and add onion and garlic.
Lightly brown chicken; set aside.
Combine tomatoes , onion, garlic, picante sauce and olives; bring to a boil.
Add chicken and simmer until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and cook sauce on high heat until thickened.
Spoon over chicken.
Serve with tortillas.

title: aunt pam's chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shells at 350 degrees until light brown.
Mix milk and pudding mix according to pie directions.
Pour in baked pie shell and let cool to room temp.
You can top with cool whip after they cool.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in boiling salted water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, oranges and sugar; let stand in refrigerator for 2 days.
Mix jellos as directed, minus 2 cups water.
Add drained pineapple and cranberry-orange mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: grandmother's aspic(salad)
directions: Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup water.
Pour V-8 juice into large pot; heat to boiling.
While heating juice, combine celery, onion, olives and nuts in bowl.
When juice has reached boiling point, add gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool somewhat.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Add salt to taste.
Add other ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Pour into greased Bundt mold or other large mold.
Let jell until very firm.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add 1 1/2 cups of tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Mix well.
Line bottom of baking dish with 2 cups Doritos chips.
Crush remaining Doritos chips and set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over Doritos.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and crushed Doritos; return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: A great breakfast food for the man who loves to cook, but never learned how!!

title: snow balls
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Roll into bite size balls. Roll in coconut and store in refrigerator.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Pour pie filling over this and chill for several hours.

title: josie's spanish rice
directions: Melt oleo (or oil) in large skillet or 3 quart saucepan.
Add uncooked rice and cook over moderate heat until golden brown, stirring often.
Add onion, salt, black pepper, garlic and bell pepper; cook until onions are lightly browned.
Stir in chili powder and tomato; cook 30 seconds longer.
Add cumin and broth, return to boil.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry until almost crisp.
Add onion and bell pepper and saute until onion is see through.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 400°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Rinse chicken.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan until very tender.
Bone and chop chicken; reserve broth.
Cook spaghetti and green pepper in reserved broth in saucepan for 15 minutes; drain. Combine with chicken, pimentos and soup in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese fine.
Add cut up pimentos.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add garlic salt, pepper, a little salt and a drop or two of Tabasco sauce, if desired.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hamburger macaroni soup
directions: Crumble beef in a 5-quart microwave casserole dish with lid. Add onion.
Cook on High 6 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Cook on High 2 minutes more.
Drain off fat again.
Add tomatoes, broth, water, macaroni, sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Cook on High 15 minutes.
Stir twice.
Add veggies and stir to break up.
Cook, covered, on High for 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
May top with shredded cheese.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: angelic strawberries and cream
directions: Mix all ingredients by folding.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: billy bob's cheese soup
directions: Chop medium onion and saute in stick of margarine.
Gradually add 1/2 cup flour.
Put in heavy saucepan.
Add 2 cans chicken broth and 4 cups milk.
Add both jars Cheez Whiz and 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper.
Boil carrots and green onions in 2 cups water for 5 minutes, then drain and add to rest of soup.
Cook over low heat until cheeses are melted and everything is good and hot.
Watch closely so it won't scorch.

title: 2 squash pies(deep-dish)
directions: Mix squash with milk. Mix all together. Bake in 2 deep-dish crusts 40 minutes at 450°. Good!

title: pork adobo
directions: Place pork in a saucepan. Add vinegar, garlic, pepper, salt or toyo to taste and water. Cover and cook slowly until meat is tender and most of the broth has evaporated, leaving only 1/4 cup. Drain. Separate pieces of garlic from pork and fry in lard until brown. Add the pieces of pork and fry until brown. Add the broth and let simmer about 5 minutes. Serve hot with rice.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl stir together apples and sugar, Add dry ingredients and stir well. In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir egg mixture into apple mixture.
Blend until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 50 minutes or until cake springs back. Serve with apple dessert sauce.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in 9 x 13-inch casserole and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, cover top with crushed potato chips and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan, pie filling and pineapple. Cut cube of margarine and drop on top of filling.
Sprinkle box of yellow cake mix over mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together the vanilla, sugar, eggs and margarine.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add chopped nuts and raisins to batter with apples.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: walnut wonder cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream the oleo and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add sour cream alternately with dry ingredients. Spread in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, brown sugar and white sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° in metal pan or 325° in glass pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken potato stew
directions: Rinse and dry chicken.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven, heat oil over high heat until hot.
Add chicken pieces and cook, turning until golden, 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain off any fat.
Add scallions, 2 tablespoons cilantro and the parsley.
Cook, stirring 1 minute. Mix in chicken broth, cumin, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in carrots and potatoes.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir in corn, capers and cream.
Simmer, uncovered, until potatoes and carrots are tender and sauce has thickened slightly, 10 to 15 minutes. Garnish with remaining 2 tablespoons cilantro.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Make
your
Fortune first so they are ready to go.
Mix together
flour, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
In another bowl, mix together the butter, oil and eggs.
Add this to the flour mixture and
mix well.
Then add the water and extract.
Stir until
all ingredients
are
mixed well.
Set oven to 300° to 325°.

title: suzan's punch
directions: Make up the can of frozen concentrate ("Twister").
Chill. Add the ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour mixture in pan with butter.
Do not stir.
Scatter fruit over mixture.
Put in oven at 350°.
Do not stir.
Cook until brown.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave oven 10 minutes at High; stir after 5 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving. Makes 3 cups.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown onions; add meat and saute until browned.
Add soup, 1 cup water, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer.
Add rice; mix and turn into casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs or grated cheese.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, onion, mustard and salt in a blender. Blend until smooth.
With machine running, gradually add oil until all has been incorporated.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: almond delight
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix butter, sugar, flour, coconut and almonds together (this should be crumbly).
Bake for 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven; stir every 5 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream the margarine or butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and Cool Whip; mix well.
Combine milk, pudding and vanilla. Let this mixture set.
Add mixture to margarine and cream cheese mixture.
Layer this in a trifle bowl, making 4 layers of dirt and 3 layers of cream cheese mixture.
This dessert may be decorated with flowers (plastic), or gummy worms may be hidden in the mixture for some real fun.
Watch their faces!
This dessert keeps well and gets better as it sets.

title: sweet-sour beef
directions: Place steak in shallow dish.
Add 3/4 cup soy sauce; mix well so all the beef will marinate.
Allow to stand at least 30 minutes.
Cook pepper strips in salad oil until limp and glazed; do not overcook.
Remove from pan.
Add beef to skillet; cook quickly, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and add pineapple juice and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add tidbits and peppers.

title: pecan pear muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. In another bowl, combine the eggs, oil and vanilla; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in the pears and pecans. Fill paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add remaining ingredients, except coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: irish oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add 1 teaspoon of honey. Combine skim milk powder and 1 cup water with wire whisk, and heat until almost to the scalding point.
Add oil, salt, and honey.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: microwave fudge (peanut butter)
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in the microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes. Add powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Mix well with hands and pat into a buttered dish. Allow to set, then cut and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cover bottom of dish with frozen French fries, 2 inches thick; put beans on fries.
Brown hamburger meat and lay on potatoes and beans.
Mix both soups and pour on other ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350° in covered dish.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine water, egg and vinegar. Add remaining ingredients. This will keep in refrigerator to be used as needed.

title: chicken tarragon in the pot
directions: Sprinkle chicken inside and out with tarragon, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in large heavy casserole or Dutch oven; cover and bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion around chicken.
Stir to combine with pan juices.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.
(If not using green pepper, bake 30 minutes.) Add green pepper; cover and bake 10 minutes. Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Use kitchen shears to cut into serving pieces.

title: strawberry jam
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place berries and pectin.
Stir well. Cover.
Place in microwave oven and heat at Full power for 8 to 10 minutes, until mixture is at a rolling boil.
Add sugar to boiling mixture and stir well.
Return, uncovered, to microwave oven and heat at Full power 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes, until mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Let boil 1 minute longer.

title: danish rice pudding
directions: Melt butter in boiler; add milk and cook rice in milk over very low heat until all milk has been absorbed, 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.
This can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated until needed.
Before serving, add the whipped cream, vanilla and almonds.
Serve with fruit sauce or syrup.

title: pizza-on-a-plate(microwave)
directions: On each of two 12-inch pieces of wax paper, press 1/2 of dough to form a 9-inch circle.
Press perforations together to seal. Brush each lightly with cooking oil.
Place wax paper on microwave ovenproof plates.
Microwave one pizza at a time. Microwave (Medium-high) 2 minutes.
Hold wax paper, flip dough over onto plate and carefully peel off wax paper. Microwave (Medium-high) 1 to 2 minutes more, until set and crisp.
There will be some brown spots.

title: hot tea punch
directions: Bring water to boil and add sugar and tea bags.
Let steep. Remove bags and add cloves and cinnamon.
Let stand for 30 minutes. Add Jello, cranberry juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve hot or cold.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs together thoroughly. Combine the buttermilk and vinegar in a cup.
Combine the dry ingredients in a large sifter.
Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Add food coloring and flavoring.
Bake in two 9 inch cake pans which have been greased and waxed-paper-lined on the bottom.
Bake at 300 degrees for about 40 minutes or until done.
Frost with cream cheese icing.
Nuts may be put right in icing or used to decorate the sides of the cake.

title: gala cocktail
directions: Fill 10 ounce glass 1/2 full with crushed ice.
Add juice, Port and bitters; stir.
Spear celery slices and olive alternately on toothpick; garnish glass with the kabob.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix ingredients (water or other fluid to proper consistency). Simmer for 1 hour.
Ready for sandwich or serving.

title: brownie cups
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spray cups of a mini muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. Prepare brownie mix according to directions for cake-like brownies. Using small scoop, fill each cup 2/3 full. Bake 14 minutes or until edges are set (do not overbake). Remove pan to cooling rack. Immediately press tops of brownie with a tart shaper to make indentations. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Loosen edges and gently remove the brownies from pan. Cool completely. Repeat with remaining batter.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Mix dough and roll thin.
I bake these first, then put filling between to make a sandwich cookie.

title: raspberry cranberry jello
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 1 hour or until Jell-O begins to set. Beat until fluffy.
Add 1 can of cranberry sauce and chill.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add vinegar to milk; mix with flour mixture immediately.
Divide dough and roll out.
Makes pastry for two pie shells.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to box directions.
Add browned beef and all other ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan stuffed shrimp
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and set aside.
Peel shrimp, devein and butterfly.
Place on cookie sheet.
Fill each shrimp with cracker mixture.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.
Then broil 1 minute until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with lemon wedges on "bed" of rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan (spray pan with Pam).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mocha java
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: cheese broccoli dip
directions: Mix cans of condensed soup (do not add water or milk) and heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add thawed broccoli and mix well.
Keep warm in fondue or chafing dish.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook pasta; drain and set aside.
Cook vegetables together and drain.
Add pasta to vegetables.
Add ham and cheese.
Mix.
Add mushroom soup.
Top with bread crumbs; sprinkle with paprika. Brown top at 350°.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Proceed as for any sweet dough.
After second rising, brush loaves with egg wash before baking.
(Egg wash, well beaten eggs.)

title: broken-glass candy
directions: Melt chocolate and
margarine
in
double boiler; cool, add marshmallows and
nuts.
Sprinkle coconut on cookie sheet; pour mixture on this.
Makes
1 or 2 rolls.
Refrigerate until hard. Slice and serve.

title: 3 minute softball parent breakfast
directions: In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, frozen snipped chives and a dash of pepper.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Pour into a microsafe 10 ounce custard cup or microsafe dish.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until almost set, pushing cooked portions to the center every 30 seconds.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Cheddar cheese.
Let stand until set.
Makes 1 serving.

title: hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers and slice.
Slice wieners.
In a large skillet combine catsup, vinegar, sugar, oil and salt and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Add peppers and wieners.
Return to boiling again.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Process in boiling bath for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 5 quarts.

title: hummus
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Use as spread, dip or dressing.

title: fluff salad
directions: Fold pie filling into Eagle Brand milk. Fold in crushed pineapple and then fold in Cool Whip. I put all ingredients in the refrigerator the night before I make. Will keep at least 2 days in refrigerator.

title: sara's christmas cake or poor man's cake
directions: Cover raisins with water and boil gently for 10 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins and mix with water from raisins.
Add beaten eggs, melted shortening and chopped nuts. Pour batter into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: caramel candy
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar in iron skillet until browned.
Cook 2 cups sugar, milk and butter until soft ball stage.
Add browned sugar to this and cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add soda.
This boils up fast when soda is added (be careful).
Beat and add nuts.

title: buffalo wings(makes 48 appetizers)
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings (save tips for a soup).
Cut chicken wings in half at joint.
In food processor or blender, process golden onion soup mix, margarine, vinegar, water, garlic, pepper and cumin until blended; set aside.
tags: Recipe Secrets golden onion soup mix

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make medium size meat balls.
Wet hands as you make each ball.
Fry in frying pan and brown well. You can use these meat balls in your spaghetti sauce and serve with spaghetti and a salad.

title: spicy chili dip
directions: Cook turkey and chopped onion in a bowl in the microwave with a piece of wax paper over it.
Cook on High about 2 to 3 minutes. Check and stir.
Cook longer if needed.
Remove turkey and onion from bowl; drain off fat.
Prepare taco mix with the microwave instructions that are on back of package.
Use only 1/4 cup water. Stir in the chopped green chilies and chopped tomato.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serve hot with low-fat tortilla chips.

title: chicken-asparagus casserole
directions: Place layer of chicken in baking dish.
Top with layer of asparagus, another layer of chicken and more asparagus.
Top with mushroom soup, thinned with juice from asparagus.
Cook 15 to 25 minutes.
Add fried onions and a few almonds.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Melt butter, Crisco and broth.
Add milk, then salt and egg. Stir in flour and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out thin and cut in strips.
Bring chicken and broth to a boil and drop dumplings in and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: annette funicello's peanut butter pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil and remove from pan.
Put peanut butter and soup in pan and heat, adding water gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add chops and onion and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 50 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt with pastry blender.
Beat egg in cup and add cold water to 1 cup.
Add vinegar and baking powder. Stir.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir lightly with fork.
Chill. Roll.
Will make 4 (2 crust) pies.
This is a nice flaky pie crust and freezes well in pies.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes and thicken with flour, sugar and water.	Add baked biscuits, broken into pieces.
Put into a baking dish.
Dot with 1/2 stick butter and bake at 350° until brown.

title: ma's chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Simmer a few minutes. Keep stirring every few minutes as it burns quickly.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer on low heat about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Taste to see if you have enough seasonings.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl and stir until well blended.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except almonds and potato chips).
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle almonds, then chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions; drain off grease. Add rest of ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake another 30 minutes.

title: mezetti
directions: Place crumbled beef, green pepper and onion in water-soaked clay pot.
Cover with water-soaked lid.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add chili powder and garlic salt.
Spread noodles over meat.
Mix soups and water together and pour over noodles.
Cover with water-soaked lid.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, then on simmer for 18 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar, salt and raisins in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix eggs, vanilla and nutmeg in 1-quart casserole. Slowly stir in rice mixture and blend well.
Place casserole in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is set.
Cool at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine flour with cornmeal and sugar.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add to flour mixture, stirring well.
Dip franks in a bowl of flour; then cover with batter.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Makes 10.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese and add seasoning.
Add onions, olives and ham.
Spread on tortillas and roll.
Cut in slices 1/3-inch thick.

title: broccoli and ham braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients, except dough and egg, in large bowl; set aside. Unroll dough on baking sheet and press all seams together. Cut 1 x 3-inch strips on the two long ends. Place mixture in center of dough. Braid the dough:

title: baked fish
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Bake fish for 15 minutes on a lightly greased baking pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients together in a bowl and spread over fish.
Cover the fish with water and bake for another 15 minutes or until fish is done and sauce is thick.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Form into a loaf or roll.
Put a few slices of bacon over the top.
Pour tomato juice over the top.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend together flour, soda, salt, eggs, bananas and milk. Beat until smooth; add lemon or vinegar and nuts.
Put in well-greased and floured 13-inch pan (or loaf pan).
Cook at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly; while still warm, put oleo on top.
Turn on wire rack until cool.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place popped corn in a large bowl and place in oven to keep warm.
Butter inside of the saucepan.
Add sugar, water, salt, corn syrup and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until reaches 250°.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and peanut butter chips, stirring until chips are almost melted.
Remove hot popcorn from oven.
Pour mixture over popcorn and stir until all the corn is coated.
With buttered hands, shape mixture into 2-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
When cool, wrap each ball in plastic wrap.
Makes 32.

title: double pie crust
directions: Add all dry ingredients; then add 5 to 6 tablespoons of cold water.
Knead into a ball.
Flour bread board; then roll out into a pie crust.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter, beat in egg.
Add mandarin juice and peel, mix thoroughly.
Mix flour, baking soda and baking powder together, add to butter mixture.
Drop batter from a teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Frost with Mandarin Icing.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: stormy weather picante sauce
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes or until desired thickness, stirring constantly.
Pour boiling hot mixture into sterilized jars.
Seal immediately.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Follow instructions on pie crust box for bottom pie crust. Mix ingredients together.
Pour on top of bottom pie crust.
Put top crust on.
Brush top of crust with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.
Cool and peel, then grate. Heat cheese and butter; melt.
Blend in milk, onion and seasoning.
Add potatoes.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill about one hour.
Serve with fruit salad.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together and pour into ungreased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients; stir on medium heat until thick.
Bake pie crust.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Add meringue; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ho ho bars
directions: Mix chocolate cake as directed. Bake in jelly roll pan.
Cool. Combine remaining ingredients. Whip 10 minutes with mixer or until creamy. Spread on cake. Cool.
Heat 1 can chocolate frosting until runny or microwave 20 seconds or until runny.
Pour over top of white spread mixture.
Spread and chill.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and set aside.
Cut next three ingredients finely.

title: easy layered salad
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer lettuce, green pepper, onions and peas.
Do not toss.
Spread salad dressing over all.
Sprinkle on bacon if desired.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl of food processor.
Pulse until mix resembles coarse meal.
In large baking pan, combine apples and cranberries with sugar and lemon juice.
Top with crisp topping and bake for 25 to 40 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and shortening until crumbly.
Add buttermilk until dough leaves sides of bowl but is not sticky.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter, or form with hands.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and cocoa to boil, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vinegar.
Boil, stirring occasionally to avoid burning, until soft ball is formed in cold water.
Remove from heat and allow to cool to lukewarm without stirring, then beat until it loses its shiny appearance.
Add nuts and vanilla when it begins to hold its shape.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix altogether and cover with a top crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix sour cream and dry onion soup real well.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Goes well with any raw vegetables or any chips.

title: chicken shepherds pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone. Cook potatoes, then mash and season to taste. In 9 x 12 pan, put soup (no water) to cover bottom. Layer corn, green beans, chicken pieces and American cheese. Cover with mashed potatoes. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Great reheated in microwave with butter on top.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: cheesey vegetable corn chowder
directions: Mix together and cook until slightly thick.

title: chicken-sesame salad
directions: For dressing, in a screw-top jar, combine salad oil, vinegar, sesame seed, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and shake well to mix. Chill thoroughly.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix and roll into small walnut size balls; flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Decorate with cherries.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer until lumps are gone and creamy. Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening. Blend in sugar and bananas until smooth. Add beaten eggs, then flour mixed with baking soda and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 3/4 to 1 hour at 350°.

title: brazilian breakfast blend
directions: Mash the banana with a fork to make a smooth texture.
Add oats and cinnamon and sweeten to taste.
Brazilian children eat this as an after school snack and they can easily make it by themselves.

title: carolyn's corn-green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix with soup, onion, cheese, water chestnuts and sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dribble margarine over this.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as per package. Mix with corn and soup. Place in casserole dish. Cover with cheese. Bake until bubbling.

title: stroganoff pork chops
directions: Cut 3 to 4 pounds roast into bite size chunks removing fat in the process.
Place meat in an oven roaster.
Apply salt and pepper.
Add water until meat is barely covered.
Use 1 1/2 teaspoons beef bouillon crystals per cup of water.
Add 1 cup chopped onions, optional.
Cook at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Turn down to 250° for 2 to 3 hours until you think that it is done.
Do not lift cover during cooking time.

title: favorite strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Wash and place strawberries in shell.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Add jello and let cool for few minutes.
Pour over berries and place in refrigerator to chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Saute onion and green chilies in margarine until limp.
Include the chili liquid.
Add cream cheese and chicken.
Simmer.

title: candied fruitcake
directions: Cut dates, pineapple, cherries and pecans in large pieces. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and gradually beat in sugar and flour mixture.
Combine with fruit. Cover with brown paper.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. When done and cooled off, brush with white Karo syrup.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat and onions with 3 tablespoons brown gravy sauce. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer until thick.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown bacon in iron skillet.
Remove bacon and set aside. Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes, salt, Worcestershire and catsup.
Crumble bacon and return to skillet.
Simmer sauce uncovered for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until thickened.
Add shrimp a few at a time.
Add sugar. Simmer about 10 minutes after last shrimp have been added.
Serve over rice.
(Serves 6 to 8.)

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt oleo and cheese over medium heat.
Add cocoa, remove from heat.
Add vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan. Put in refrigerator to set.
Cut in squares.
Can store out of refrigerator.

title: pickled beets and onions
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, vinegar, water and cloves.
Drain jar of beets and put in a bowl with onions.
Pour vinegar mixture over beets.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: wine sauerkraut
directions: In butter, saute onion and apple for 2 minutes.
Add sauerkraut, wine, bay leaf and pepper.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add grapes.
Heat through but do not boil again.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: terry's barbecue sauce
directions: To begin, you need something big enough to cook a hog in (ours is made from a 250 gallon butane gas tank; a cooker made from concrete blocks, stacked up to form the walk, and a make shift grill to hold the meat and laid on top, will also work).

title: sally lunn(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix and cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix alternately with milk.
Add flavoring last.
Start in cold oven.
Set at 350°.
Cook 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven door during this time.

title: spaghetti with clams
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
In a small pan, saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until clams are heated through.
Pour over pasta.
Serves 2.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Drain chickpeas and rinse.
Mince garlic.
Pit olives and slice.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
In a small jar, shake together vinegar, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper until salt dissolves.
Add oil and shake again to combine.
Pour this dressing over chickpea mixture and toss.
Serves 6.

title: 3 soup casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Cook noodles and drain.
In a large baking dish, put all ingredients and stir to mix well.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Cheese cut in small chunks may be added before baking.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
When done, pull meat apart and mix with sauce.

title: eggless pumpkin pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, except sugar. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Add sugar and then milk which has been scalded.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake until firm
in the center, about 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Pour pecans and coconut in bottom of pan; set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine sugars and butter.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans, fruit and raisins.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients, except crumbs and peppers.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Place green pepper or pimento strips across top.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: chickpea soup
directions: Wash and pick over chickpeas; bring to a boil with stock and pork; simmer for 3 hours.
Add vegetables and seasonings; simmer for 30 minutes more.
Mash about 1/2 of the chickpeas and vegetables into the soup to give it a rough texture.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a flat pan.
Place onion rings on top of chops.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Stir about halfway through baking time.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin and cream cheese; stir until smooth. Cool.
Add all other ingredients; put in oiled mold.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: beef burrito casserole
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and put in bottom of 13 x 9 dish. Layer top with hamburger, salt and cheese. Add olives. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with lettuce and sour cream.

title: dorothy's fudge
directions: Put first 3 items in mixing bowl and set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter; bring to boil on high heat, stirring constantly.
When syrup boils, lower heat.
Stir and cook for 6 minutes.
Pour syrup over chocolate and Marshmallow Creme, beating until blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool for 24 hours (at room temperature).
Score and cut into squares.
Store in airtight container up to 2 weeks.
Do not refrigerate.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish. Combine dressing, preserves, soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well and pour over chicken. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered. Good served with rice.

title: cooked shrimp(microwave)
directions: Place shrimp in 1-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on full power for 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until shrimp are pink and opaque.
Drain shrimp.
Cover and chill.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 1 1/4 cups rolled oats in the container of a food processor, process 1 minute.
Cream butter with both sugar and brown sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in the egg and vanilla.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat, then drain. Add large can of pinto beans and 1 can tomato sauce and garlic (to taste). Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes on medium low heat.

title: fresh peach sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, mix crushed peaches, sugar and orange juice.
Place over high heat and stir until boiling.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 15 minutes or until thick without covering.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and extract. Makes 2 cups.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus well.
(Use juice to thin soup, if needed.) Heat soup.
If too thick, add asparagus juice to thin.
Set aside.

title: baked fish
directions: Bake 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream well the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well.
Add crushed pineapple to bread.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish (buttered).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.

Mix well, then mix with a mixer at medium speed. Cream the butter, oil, confectioners sugar and 1 cup white sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Continue mixing. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: Pour liquids over cut up chicken.
Dot with margarine.
Place chicken mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with pie crust and bake according to directions.

title: stuffed zucchini(for those real big ones!!)
directions: Cut zucchini in half horizontally.
Scoop out seeds.
Mix meat (uncooked), onion and rice.
Fill the two halves of zucchini with this mixture.
Pour spaghetti sauce over it, then the cheeses. Place in a roaster pan both halves face up.
Put small amount of water in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until meat is done and squash is tender.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until light and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Gently stir into zucchini mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Pour macaroni on bottom of cake pan. Pour macaroni on bottom of cake pan. Cut up stick of butter and put on macaroni. Sprinkle all the cheeses on and last pour milk on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Check, then cover and bake another 30 minutes with aluminum foil so it doesn't burn.

title: easy icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Cover dough with waxed paper and refrigerate overnight (or at least 4 hours).
Two or three hours before baking, take out dough and knead for 3 minutes.
Roll out for dinner rolls.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Grease center of circle with table knife.
Put a tiny dot of butter in center of crease and fold over for pocketbook rolls; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: "poultry days" barbecue marinade"
directions: Mix all together in a large pot until dissolved.

title: lo-cal dip(microwave)
directions: In microwave, melt cubed cream cheese and salsa until melted and warm.
Dip chips and enjoy!!!

title: blackberry cake
directions: Beat all together and place in Bundt cake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cake completely cool.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Add to diced vegetables.
Cover with the marinade and refrigerate in a covered dish, 4 to 5 hours or longer before serving.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients, except fruit and wafers; mix well.
Place paper bake cups in muffin pan.
Put one vanilla wafer in bottom of each bake cup.
Cover each wafer with about 2 tablespoons cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.
Cool and top each little cheesecake with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: sarah's spiced hot tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a 1 pound container with lid. Shake before using. Add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: devil cake
directions: Mix well and blend with spoon.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Cook 50 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated three bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables. In a 3-quart saucepan, combine vinegar and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables. Mix well.
Cover and chill overnight, stirring several times. To serve, drain marinade. Makes 10 to 12 servings (about 10 cups).

title: italian chicken
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Dip chicken in eggs and dredge in flour.
Brown chicken in melted margarine.
Transfer chicken to 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour marinara sauce and tomatoes over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: great kielbasa
directions: Bake kielbasa for 1 hour at 350°.
Pierce with fork and slice. Place in baking dish.
While kielbasa bakes, simmer sauerkraut and water, covered.
Drain and add to kielbasa.
Combine applesauce, sugar and onion.
Add to kielbasa and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot spice bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
