title: momma's italian-style spinach
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a skillet over medium heat until mixture looks "dry" (this means the egg has thoroughly cooked).
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise. Place broccoli evenly on bottom of baking dish.
Place cooked chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Spread soup mixture over all. Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cook for 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of the cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, margarine or butter and beaten egg.
Stir by hand until mixture is crumbly.
Press the mixture evenly over bottom and an inch up the sides of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile combine the three eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add the reserved cake mix. Stir by hand.
Spread filling evenly over the crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: soda-pop gelatin(child's recipe)
directions: Make gelatin according to box but substitute seltzer water for 1 cup cold water.
Add fruit.
Mix well and chill.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick oleo. Set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Add eggs, flour, buttermilk and soda.
Add melted candy, oleo mixture and pecans.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: dumpling squares
directions: Beat together egg, milk and butter.
Stir into dry ingredients. Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead a few times to make a smooth dough.
Roll out to 8 x 8-inch square.
Cut into 16 (2-inch) squares.
Drop into boiling broth and simmer, covered until tender, about 20 minutes to half hour.

title: shepherd pie casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt, pepper and onion.
Drain beef well.
Cook potatoes and mash.
Put beef, corn and carrots in a pan.
Add mashed potatoes over them.
Cook for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add flour to yeast mixture; mix and knead.
Add flour until not sticky and smooth round balls.
Put in bowl; cover and let rise 15 to 30 minutes.
Spread dough on greased cookie sheet.
Pour on 1 can (or to taste) tomato sauce.
Top with meat, Romano, salt, oregano, Parmesan, mushrooms or any topping you prefer.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then add Mozzarella and bake 10 minutes more.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Mix, put in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.
Uncover, top with buttered crumbs. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: easter omelette
directions: Mix eggs and Ricotta cheese.
Slice sausage and bake for about 20 to 25 minutes (until no longer pink).
Pour egg mixture over sausage and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
(Insert fork or knife; should come out clean when done.)

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garden salad
directions: Pour over tomatoes, cucumbers, green peppers, celery and onions.
Let set overnight.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Separate eggs.
Save yolks for future use.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Leave beaters in the whites for now.
Put sugar and water in saucepan over medium heat.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In casserole dish, stir in noodles, tuna, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: low-fat golden fish nuggets with dilled tartar sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Combine cornflake crumbs and next 3 ingredients in a shallow bowl; set aside.
Place egg white in bowl.
Dip fish in egg white and crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes or until crispy and browned.
Serve with sauce.
This recipe makes 2 servings; may double, triple for more.

title: knaddles
directions: Into medium size pan, boil water while you mix the eggs, milk, salt and flour.
Drop by teaspoonful into boiling water.
When dumplings float, they are finished.
Remove; drain.
Add butter. Serve.

title: diet fudge brownies
directions: Mix sugar, sugar substitute, margarine, eggs, Butter Buds and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar; blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with sliced strawberries, peaches, cherries, mandarin orange slices, your choice.

title: seven-up punch
directions: Chill fruits, pineapple juice and 7-Up. Combine pineapple and strawberries in punch bowl; stir in pineapple juice.
Pour in 7-Up slowly; mix gently. Add 2 trays ice cubes; garnish punch bowl with orange rind curls. Yields about 30 servings.

title: potato candy
directions: Beat egg white until stiff. Stir in lemon juice, salt and sugar. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over waxed paper. Pour mixture onto this. Roll it out about 1 inch thick. Spread peanut butter on top of this. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place in refrigerator until ready to slice.

title: caramel candy
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper.
Chill.
Melt shortening and chocolate morsels in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Dip candy into chocolate and return to waxed paper. Chill.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and pat dry mushrooms.
Remove stems and save.
Put caps in baking dish, open side up.
Cut ends off stems, discard.
Dice stems fine.
In bowl combine diced stems, onion, celery, Ricotta and egg; mix well.
Soften or slightly melt butter.
Add and mix; season.
Add bread crumbs until mixture is not watery, firm, but not crumbly.
Fill mushroom caps, piled high.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave 7 to 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix with hands; make little round rolls.
May freeze after you cook for later.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Put an extra pan under it to keep bottom from browning too fast.

title: chicken 'n crescent
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add chicken, chives, pepper, salt and milk.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles. Put 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto rectangles.
Pull corners up to center and seal.
Brush with 1 tablespoon oleo and dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake in ungreased baking dish (uncovered) at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: bayou baked red snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Clean fish and pat dry. Rub cavity with salt, pepper and butter. Place in well-greased baking pan and set aside. Heat 3 to 4 Tbsp. butter in heavy skillet. Add shallots and saute until soft but not brown. Add more butter and mushrooms, continue cooking - shaking pan until most butter is absorbed. Stir in oregano and pour mixture over fish. Bake fish 12 minutes per inch of thickness. Baste several times while baking.

title: strawberry banana whip
directions: Prepare gelatin with hot water; add ice cubes after gelatin is dissolved.
Transfer to blender.
Add banana and yogurt.
Puree on low speed.
Divide into 4 cups.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with 1/4 berries added to top to garnish.
Serves 4. Contains 45 calories, 1 gm fat and 80 mg sodium.

title: pear and apple chutney
directions: Combine all and boil, then simmer 1 hour and 40 minutes. Store 2 weeks.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook on low heat, stirring occasionally until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cajun fish
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook green pepper with oregano until tender, stirring often.
Add soup, water, garlic powder, black pepper and red pepper.
Heat to boiling.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread coconut evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash.
Chop onion and saute lightly in margarine.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine onion and margarine (it was sauteed in) with slightly beaten eggs.
Add cream of chicken soup (undiluted), mashed squash, cornbread, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a skillet and saute onions.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix well.
Have frozen hash browns thawed out some; mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Mix the melted margarine and corn flakes.
Pat into crust over the potatoes during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mash cream cheese flat on sides of serving dish, including bottom. Glass pan is best. Layer onions or jalapeos, if desired. Pour in chili and top with cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck and onion.
Add chili mix, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer until desired consistency.
If not spicy enough, add hot sauce or chili powder. Makes about 1 quart.
Freezes well for later use.

title: sauerkraut-rice-meat casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown lightly the sausage, hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain rice.
Layer mixture, rice and sauerkraut in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with a layer of meat mixture on the bottom and top.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fold in 3 1/2 ounces chips (crushed by hand).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top after baking.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per box directions and place in a prepared sheet pan.
When you take it out of the oven, immediately poke holes in it with a fork (all over the top of the cake).
Pour on the can of condensed milk.
Let that saturate the cake and then immediately pour on the jar of ice cream topping.
Let cake cool completely in pan and then frost with the Cool Whip.
Top with chopped Heath bars.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach-fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit reserving one tablespoon of juice.
Combine spinach and fruit.
Mix mayonnaise with juice and toss.

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter a casserole and after you have mixed the ingredients, pour mixture into the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Warm vinegar to dissolve sugar.
Mix and put in refrigerator. Marinate at least 24 hours before eating.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix M&M's, popcorn and peanuts.
Heat oil, oleo and marshmallows until melted.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir. Butter angel food cake pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Leave set in pan for couple of hours.
Turn over on plate.
Should come out easy.

title: vanilla candy
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly.
To prevent scorching, remove from heat.
Gradually stir in vanilla chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature. Makes 3 pounds.
Do not substitute sweetened condensed milk.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt oleo; put in crumbs.
Put 1/2 mixture of crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Mix other ingredients.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender or with a Mixmaster until creamy.
If it is too thick, add a little milk.
The Kraft Miracle French dressing is the secret to this recipe.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Pour off juice from cherries in a measuring cup and finish filling with milk.
Mix and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: graham cracker crumb cake
directions: Start with crumbs.
Add ingredients as listed, mixing well after each addition.

title: venison marinade
directions: This will usually tenderize the meat within 24 hours but 48 takes much of the "wild" taste out of the meat.
Great with long grain and wild rice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash
and
remove
stems
from mushrooms.
Dip mushroom caps in	lemon juice and lightly salt the cavity of mushroom. Arrange on baking pan.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs and diced mushroom stems
together, fill the mushrooms with mixture and top each
one with a small piece of fried bacon.	Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: crab cakes
directions: In a large stainless-steel bowl, combine all ingredients except crab meat and bread crumbs.	Using gloves, gently mix in crabmeat, then add bread crumbs.
Spread a thin layer of plain bread crumbs on a work surface.
Form crab mixture into balls and place on crumbs.
Gently flatten balls and form cakes about 1/2 inch thick.
Refrigerate.
In a saut pan, heat oil and gently slide cakes and brown two at a time.
Brown on each side approximately 2-3 minutes.	Turn down heat to simmer and cook another 5-8 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Moisten bread cubes with the milk. Mix with remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or for 45 minutes at 375° in a 2-quart covered dish or 9-inch square pan. Serve warm.

title: orange eggnog punch
directions: In bowl, place all but 1 cup sherbet.
Beat until smooth.
Add juices and blend thoroughly.
Gradually add eggnog.
Pour into punch bowl.
Float small scoops of sherbet on top.

title: vernaughn's buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk and soda.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add butter and pecans.
Boil 5 minutes longer. Cool slightly and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: never fail chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Put margarine, cocoa and milk on stove and let come to a rolling boil.
Take off stove and add vanilla and stir.

title: methodist punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into container.
Add ice.
Will fill punch bowl.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into a greased baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.

title: chocolate butter frosting with pecans
directions: Mix softened butter or oleo.
Add salt, powdered sugar, chocolate syrup and milk; beat until fluffy with electric beater. Add vanilla and pecans; continue beating until nuts have been properly mixed into the frosting.

title: smothered steak
directions: Mix flour with seasonings and use to dredge meat.
Heat fat in skillet and brown meat on both sides.
Cover steak with onions, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add dash of hot pepper sauce.
Roast in preheated oven at 300° for 2 hours or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick bake
directions: Combine applesauce and ginger.
Spread in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Lightly score meat slices and stud with cloves.
Put potatoes and meat on applesauce.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over meat and potatoes.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on well greased cookie sheet.
Bake until firm to touch.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add all dry ingredients.
When this is mixed, add M&M's.
Reserve some to add to the top of some cookies that don't have many on them. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage as for slaw.
Add onions, peppers, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric and salt.
Heat vinegar and brown sugar. Pour over mixture and mix well.
Pack in jars and seal.
Hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: Blend in blender until mixed.
Spoon into sherbet glasses. Serve chilled.
A real treat for your family or special guests.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix oleo with soup; cool.
Add sour cream.
Combine potatoes, cheese and onion, then mix with soup mix and salt and pepper. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot top with butter and crumbs. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: A day before, cut the fruits and soak in grape juice.
Next day, mix in the nuts, lemon juice and peel.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing continuously.
Add flour. Add the fruits and spices.
Pour into a mold and bake at 325°.

title: crabmeat and artichoke casserole(yields 10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Warm half and half slowly in a saucepan; make a cream sauce in a Teflon skillet.
Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Add flour and blend with a wire whisk. Slowly stir in hot cream; add white pepper, salt, Tabasco and mace and cook until smooth and boiling; continue stirring.
Adjust seasonings; more salt may be needed.
Add Sauterne.

title: herbed seafood sauce
directions: Mix pickles, onion, parsley and garlic.
Put in sieve.
Press to extract as much juice as possible.
Add juice to mayonnaise. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve sauce or dip with seafood.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Pour beaten eggs over flour mixture. Add milk, then butter.
Fold together until flour is just moistened.
Cook in hot greased skillet until done.

title: butterscotch broiler frosting
directions: Melt together oleo and milk.
Add sugar, coconut and nuts. Spread over warm, freshly baked cake.
(A spice or chocolate cake is good.)
Place on 2nd shelf under broiler and broil until brown and bubbly.
Watch to be sure not to overcook or burn!
Good!

title: health salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the hot water in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Whip the Jell-O and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Holds well in refrigerator.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat until fluffy.
Spread evenly over hot mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Mash potatoes; add cream cheese, egg, dash of salt and pepper. Beat until smooth.
Stir in onion.
If mixture seems dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.
Place in buttered quart casserole and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat until melted.
Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with soda crackers.
Pour hot mixture over crackers and bake for 10 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.
Break apart when cooled.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat mixture and pour over cooked potatoes.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Depending on the quantity of potatoes cooked, you may have enough mixture to use for another meal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar to soft ball stage.
Take off stove and put in butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Let set until cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken burgundy
directions: Roll chicken thoroughly in flour. Fry in saucepan with butter, ham, mushrooms and onions until golden brown. Add salt, pepper, bay leaf, cloves, garlic and wine.
Cover and cook in a moderate oven at 350° for at least 45 minutes, adding a little water during cooking, if necessary. When done, turn out on the serving dish and deep warm.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Cook ground beef, salt, onion, celery and green pepper. Drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer awhile to blend flavors.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients gently by hand.
(Try not to squish the cherries!)
Bake according to cake mix directions.*
Good to top/frost with Cool Whip.

title: deluxe lima beans
directions: Soak and cook lima beans for about 1/2 hour; drain.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Add beans to mixture.
Bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine oil and next 4 ingredients. Drizzle over tomato mixture and toss gently. Cover and refrigerate no longer than 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chops.
Yield 5 cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in very large bowl in order given. Drop by large tablespoonfuls and flatten.
Bake for 12 minutes (do not overbake).
They spread out when baking.
They freeze well.

title: lemon-apricot chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spread 1 tablespoon of melted margarine in jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Beat egg and water slightly.
Mix baking mix, lemon peel and garlic powder.
Flatten chicken breasts to 1/2 inch thickness.
Dip in egg mixture, then coat with baking mix.
Place chicken in pan, drizzle with remaining melted margarine.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes.
Turn; bake 10 minutes longer.
Prepare sauce.
Cut chicken crosswise into 1/2 inch slices.
Pour sauce over.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: *When avocados are not in season, I use a store bought avocado dip and cut back on the sour cream mixture.

title: chili cheese dip(so easy!)
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add can of chili and the diced chilies (if you like) and mix with a spoon.
Microwave for 1 minute on High.
Blend well and put into a pie or quiche dish.
Top with 1 to 2 cups of Cheddar cheese and put in a preheated 325° oven until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: potato salad for 50
directions: Cook the potatoes in a steamer, if possible.
When tender, cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and add mayonnaise.
This can be flavored to taste with mustard, pickle juice, pepper and any other flavorings you wish.

title: mom's sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all but the last 2 ingredients.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and pour over mixture.
Stir.
Let cool to refrigerate; refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving it.
The salad will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: diet meat loaf
directions: Line broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape meat into large patty and pour 1/2 cup tomato juice over the meat.
Bake at 340° for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until all is mixed.
Add vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts. (The pineapple and bananas make an interesting taste to this cake.)
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Makes 3 layers or 2 Bundt pans.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry jelly and lemon Jell-O; heat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until set.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream butter and sugar, stir in water and vanilla; add flour, mix thoroughly and add almonds.
Form into crescents 2-inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° until delicately browned for approximately 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Makes 2 dozen crescents.

title: maple butter icing
directions: Blend butter with sugar. Add syrup and beat mixture until well blended and fluffy. Frosts two 8-inch layers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; cool and drain.
Combine macaroni, green pepper, cucumbers, celery and hard-cooked eggs.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and chill.
Melt butter in small saucepan; add flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg and vinegar; add to butter and flour mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool slightly and add mayonnaise.
Toss dressing and macaroni mixture.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine beans in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together, blending well and add to beans.
Toss well.
Refrigerate overnight.
This makes a large amount.
Great for a large party. Makes a great summer dish when it's too hot to cook.

title: cola roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine the salt, pepper and garlic powder; rub over surface of roast.
In a Dutch oven, heat the oil to hot and brown roast on all sides.
Transfer roast to roasting pan.

title: chicken delight
directions: In a crock-pot, place chicken on bottom.
Sprinkle with paprika and celery salt.
Mix in soups (I use low-fat soups, now available in markets), sherry and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on low setting approximately 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with or over rice.

title: white suet pudding
directions: Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put in cloth bags and boil for several hours in water.
Take out and hang up where they will dry.
Take bags off and heat and brown before serving.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat well. Beat in egg.
Melt chocolate over hot water; stir into creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients; add to chocolate mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.

title: crock-pot pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet, stirring frequently. Combine remaining ingredients in crock-pot, mixing well.
Cook on low for 3 hours or to desired consistency.

title: hot mexican corn sticks
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine corn, buttermilk, egg substitute, chiles and oleo; add to cornmeal mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Coat heavily a cast-iron corn stick pan with Mazola spray.
Place in a 425° oven for 5 minutes.
Spoon batter into hot pan, fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove corn sticks from pan immediately. Yield 15 corn sticks (80 calories, 2.1 fat)

title: cornmeal tortillas
directions: Heat griddle to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add most of water and blend well to make a paste.
Add remaining water and egg; beat well.
Spoon batter onto (dry) griddle with a large mixing spoon or ladle.
Immediately spread out in a circular motion from center out.
Lift edges when able.
Turn when light brown.
Cook on second side until edges ruffle.
Cool on rack. Refry with Crisco.
For soft shell, fry briefly each side.
Hard shell, fry briefly one side, fold in half; fry each side.

title: virginia fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order (sugar, flour, soda, pineapple and pecans).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before icing.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper. Set aside.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes. Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: danish pastry filling
directions: Add 1/4 cup of crushed berries to juice.
Add cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cool; add rest of crushed berries.

title: creamy mushroom sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook mushrooms and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve with beef or poultry.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: holiday cheese log
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all except crushed walnuts.
Form mixture into 2 log shapes or balls.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with butter crackers or Hawaiian bread.

title: turkey steaks italiano
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil until hot.
Cook turkey steaks about 2 minutes on each side or until browned.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in a double boiler and let get cold.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into the custard.
Beat the pure cream until stiff and fold in.
Place in pie crust and freeze in deep freeze.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle small marshmallows on top and heat until browned.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Cream together sugar and softened butter.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and caramel syrup and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Stir only enough to mix ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in layers in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Frosting

title: strawberries and cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into pie crust.
Arrange strawberries, pointed side up, over filling.
Chill.

title: apricot angel delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and bring to a boil, stirring until thick, then cool slightly.
Break the angel food cake into bite size pieces and place them in a 10 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Pour the liquid over the cake and cool.
Then add the Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on the top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pasta figola(pronounced pasta fa'zoo)
directions: Skin snake by cutting through the skin and peeling it back until you have completely skinned the snake.
Cut into 3 to 4-inch pieces.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Combine rice, 1 1/3 cups water and salt.
Cook until rice has absorbed water.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel. To same pan, add beans, tossing until well coated with rest of ingredients.
Cover and steam for 10 minutes.
Fold beans into hot rice.
Put in serving dish.
Blend sour cream, dill weed, salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce over beans.
Top with bacon.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Drain off excess fat and add onion and peppers.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and tomato paste, oregano, garlic and salt.
Heat.
Cook spaghetti with salt; drain and cool slightly.
Stir oleo, grated Parmesan and eggs into hot spaghetti. Form into crust in buttered glass plate.
Spread cottage cheese over crust, then fill with meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: codfish with potatoes (portuguese)(batatas e bacalhau)
directions: Plan the amount of fish and potatoes for the number of persons you are serving, usually one slice of dry cod and two potatoes.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Chop sauerkraut and mix with all ingredients except bread crumbs and eggs. Cook until well browned.
Turn off heat and add bread crumbs and eggs. Chill well and form into balls. After coating (recipe to follow), bake in oven or deep fry until golden brown. Serve with your favorite dipping mustard.

title: veggie appetizer pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in sprayed pan. Press over bottom and 1-inch up the sides of pan. Seal the perforations. Bake crust for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Let cool.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Spread evenly in order given in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Cover and let set in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Lightly brown onion in salad oil.
Add combined remaining ingredients, except franks.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Split franks. Place in shallow baking dish and pour over sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: piquant green beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces, fry until crisp.
Add all other ingredients (except beans) to bacon, (do not drain bacon).
Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Add drained beans, mix well, heat thoroughly and serve.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers and onion together in a ceramic or glass bowl. Add salt, sugar and dill weed to vinegar; pour over cucumbers and onion.
Chill 1 hour.
Serves 6.
Each serving contains 20 calories.
Enjoy.

title: eight minute light and fluffy pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes. Add ice cubes and stir constantly until thickened.
(It is vital to stir constantly until thickened.)
This should take about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove unmelted ice cubes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large heavy saucepan; mix well. Gradually add water and lemon juice, stirring until smooth.

title: convent pie
directions: Cook, drain and rinse macaroni.
Add all remaining ingredients to macaroni and mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham creamette casserole
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and meat.
Cook Creamettes.
Heat milk, cheese and soup until cheese is melted; mix with first mixture.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add strawberries.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and meat.
Mix into cream cheese and roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: lentil soup
directions: In large pot, cover lentils with water and bring to a boil. Pour off water, then add about 8 cups water.
Add onion, celery, salt, potatoes and tomatoes.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Brown pork sausage in skillet.
Pour drippings into soup.
Cover and cook slowly until well done, several hours.
Add pork sausage to soup before serving.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve the yeast and honey in 1/4 cup warm water.
In a mixer fitted with dough hook, combine the flour and salt.
Pour in 2 tablespoons of the oil and when absorbed, scrape in the dissolved yeast.
Add the remaining 1/2 cup water and knead on low speed about 5 minutes (10 minutes by hand).

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut tips off wings, then cut wings at joint.
Put meat in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 25 minutes, or until browned.
Turn occasionally.
Put on platter.
Heat Tabasco, butter and vinegar; drizzle over meat.
Serve with celery and dressing for dipping.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add other dry ingredients (sifted together) alternately with the water and vanilla.
Then add dates, etc.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Spray bottom of large skillet with vegetable spray. Brown pork chops on both sides. Season with salt and pepper. Add 1/4 cup orange juice. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas and stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.
Spread whipping cream on top.

title: all seasons fruit salad
directions: Prepare fruit and combine in a large bowl; squeeze lemon juice over and mix well.
Arrange lettuce leaves on salad plates. Divide fruit among plates and serve.

title: menudo
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in large pot.
Cover with water; simmer for several hours.
Strain broth; chill reserve hominy.
Break meat off bones and reserve; chill.
When broth can be skimmed, take off fat and add hominy and meat back into broth in pot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 to 2 hours longer, until it "smells right!"
Add seasoning as needed.
Serve with side of fresh sage and limes.

title: ham and noodles
directions: In bowl, add 1 layer of noodles, 1 layer of tomatoes and chopped ham; repeat same.
Add noodles on top.
Beat the eggs and milk.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and butter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add whipping cream and flour alternately.
Add flavor. Cook in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Use a tube pan.

title: sweet potato and squash pancakes(can be used as a casserole, too)
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Spray griddle or 10-inch skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add oil.
Heat griddle over medium heat or to 375°.
Mix remaining ingredients.

title: tote'm rolls
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Stir in soup mix, oregano, salt and catsup.
Cool.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 rectangles. Seal perforations.
Divide hamburger mixture equally onto long side of each rectangle.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up lengthwise, jellyroll fashion.
Bring ends together to form a doughnut shape.
Seal ends tightly.
Brush top with milk or melted butter.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Place rolls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased square pan,9x9x2-inch; stir together flour, sugar, 2 Tbsp. cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil, and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water over batter.
DO NOT STIR.

title: sherry's queen salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and fold together carefully.
Pour into a bowl and decorate with reserved cherries.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Very colorful and pretty.

title: "slider" stew
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion in a skillet; drain off fat and put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients to crock-pot. Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 9 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While hot, spread 1 jar of marshmallow cream over top of cake.
While still warm, spread topping over it.

title: oatmeal caramel
directions: In a bowl, mix by hand the flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter, salt and soda.
Press half of the mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan, ungreased.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: clove cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Chill dough in refrigerator overnight.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Stick 1 whole clove in top of each cookie. Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven, or until light brown or golden, not dark.
While still hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs, milk, ground beef, onions, salt and sage. Mix well. Put in loaf pan. Mix catsup, brown sugar and mustard well and spread on meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Melt caramels with evaporated milk, mix until smooth.
Toast pecans and sprinkle over caramels.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Loosen it from spring-form pan. Cool completely.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil pasta until almost done.

title: herbed potato bake
directions: Mix butter, soup mix and rosemary. Toss with potatoes. Pour into shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add yolks slowly; add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour into freezer.
Add gallon of milk. Turn until thick.

title: lime marshmallow salad
directions: Pour gelatin into boiling water.
Add marshmallows and stir until all are melted.
Put in bowl and refrigerate until somewhat jellied.
Thoroughly cream the cheese with the sugar and add to jello.
Fold in whipped cream and add pears to jello.
Put into mold.
When placing on platter to serve, put fresh or sliced strawberries in center of mold.

title: spoon bread
directions: Place
corn
meal
that has been sifted before measuring and milk
in a saucepan and let come to a boil, stirring well. Remove from
fire;
add salt, shortening and sugar.
Let cool. Add baking powder and beaten egg yolks and last the egg whites which have
been
beaten
stiff.
Bake in greased casserole at 325° to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter onto a heated and lightly greased griddle.
Cook until top surface is bubbly and edges are dry.
Turn, cook until golden.
Keep pancakes warm.
Serve with syrup or honey.
Makes about 16 pancakes.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Add water in the juice to make 2 cups.
Heat to a boiling point and dissolve jello in the liquid.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Refrigerate.
If so desired, use a low-fat topping.

title: doreen's brownies
directions: Mix like any other brownies.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: glazed fruit dessert
directions: Combine pudding mix and pineapple juice. Stir until thickened. Fold in fruit.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: holly taters
directions: Put mixture into plastic bag, then add taters that are quartered.
(Small potatoes are best and cook quicker.)
Leave peelings on potatoes.
Put 3/4 stick of melted oleo in large pan and add potatoes.
Bake for 50 minutes at 400°.
Turn halfway through baking.

title: mamaw's homemade chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken, celery, bay leaves and onion together until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Remove bay leaves from broth and add carrots, noodles, salt and pepper. Cover and cook at medium heat 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from bone.
Add chicken to soup and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer. Yield: 6 servings.

title: roast curried chicken and vegetables in a bag
directions: This dinner is prepared in an oven cooking bag that seals in juices and flavors and practically eliminates cleanup.
Be sure to use bags specifically made for oven cooking, not food storage or boil-in-bags.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix and boil orange jello and pineapple in pan (2 or 3 minutes).
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and milk together.
When pineapple mixture is cool, mix cream cheese mixture in with the pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour in square dish and chill.

title: caramel chip bars
directions: In large saucepan, combine butter, caramels and milk.
Cook over medium low heat until smooth, stirring often.
Combine the cake mix, oil and eggs.
Mix well and stir in chips and chopped candy bar.
Press 3/4 into a greased 13x9 in. baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Place on wire rack for 10 minutes. Pour caramel mixture over the crust.
Drop remaining dough mixture by spoonfuls onto caramel layer.
Bake for 25-30 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Run a knife around the edges of the pan.
Cool 40 minutes longer.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Yields: 2 dozen.

title: spinach dip 'n pumpernickel(fun to make for adults and kids - requires no cooking!)
directions: Thaw and thoroughly drain spinach.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Hidden Valley (dry) with spinach.
The dip is now complete!

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Combine cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Mix and press into pan.
Beat together pumpkin pie mix, 2 eggs and milk.
Pour over crust.
Mix together the 1 cup cake mix, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into 1/4 cup margarine with fork to make crumbs.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Place under broiler for few minutes to brown top if desired.

title: pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops in oil and salt.
Drain off grease.
Mix soup, 1 can water and milk.
Pour over chops.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine and chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Stir in sugar gradually (about 4 tablespoons at a time) being sure the sugar is completely moistened after each addition.
Mixture will become very thick and dry.
Add salt and slowly stir in evaporated milk (a little at a time).
Serve hot. Makes about 1 quart of sauce.

title: cake cones for the class(makes 30 ice cream cone cakes)
directions: Chill in fridge for at least 3 hours to enrich flavor.
Heat pizzelle oven, oil it; use teaspoon to drop walnut size dough onto pans.
Burn to first batch and cook to rest light in color. Yields 8 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over hot water.
Cool slightly. Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool, then cut.
Sprinkle top with confectioners 10x sugar.
Makes 24.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw and roll bread dough to 12 x 16-inch rectangle.

title: meringues
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, adding sugar as you go, with salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Plop on tinfoil.
Bake for 60 minutes at 250° until chewy.
Take out and enjoy!!

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown onions, peppers and ground beef together.
Add taco seasoning and green chilies.
Cook unti all is mixed; drain.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Mix well and cook about 5 minutes.
Add cheese and bring to a boil.
Serve with your favorite chip.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Brush bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish with oil. Mix next 5 ingredients. Dredge chicken through mix. Arrange chicken, skin side down, in pan. Bake for 45 minutes. Turn chicken. Spread chili sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with Mozzarella. Bake for 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: hamburger casserole(entire meal)
directions: Pat raw ground beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add chopped onion to cover meat; add green beans.
Cover with undiluted mushroom and celery soup.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in medium oven. Serve immediately.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, then peel and cut up.
Cut cucumber, eggs and onion.
Add oil and vinegar, salt and pepper and bacon bits.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set for 15 minutes.

title: delicious roast beef
directions: Do not add salt.
Lay roast on heavy foil in pan.
Over roast, pour dry soup mix, can of mushroom soup and 1 small Coca-Cola. Wrap foil around roast loosely, but tightly sealed.
Bake 3 hours at 275°.
This makes its own gravy.
Ideal for Sunday lunch.

title: peach fritters
directions: Mix all together.
Keep batter thick.
Pare and quarter peaches.
Dip in batter and fry in hot oil.
Roll in sugar.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa; stir well.
Add eggs.
Stir mixture; do not heat.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: nut bread
directions: Add baking powder to flour.
Add eggs to sugar.
Add baking soda to sour cream.
Mix flour mixture to egg mixture.
Add sour cream mixture.
Add nuts.
Place batter in well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check for doneness.
If still not done in center, turn oven off and let set still in oven for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together until clear and slightly thickened first 3 ingredients.
Add jello and strawberries (cleaned and hulled). Pour into baked pie shell and chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cream wafer cookies
directions: Mix together butter, milk and flour; chill overnight.
Roll and cut with a bottle cap; roll in sugar and prick top with fork. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: creamed beef on toast or s.o.s.(as vernon sehrt and walter rice remembered it from world war 2)
directions: Chip beef
in
butter
that
has
been melted in a pan. Cook just until	well heated. Stir in flour and milk to make a smooth sauce. Serve over toast.

title: noel wreaths
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy in large bowl.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift in flour gradually, blending well to make a soft dough.
Measure out 1/4 cup dough and mix with walnuts, corn syrup and maple flavoring in small bowl.
Set aside for filling in next step.
Fit star plate or disk on cookie press. Fill with remaining dough; press out into 4-inch lengths on ungreased cookie sheets.
Join ends of each to form a circle. Fill center of each with about a teaspoonful of syrup-nut mixture; decorate with tiny "bows" of cut red and green cherries.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 15 minutes or until golden.
Remove carefully from cookie sheets; cool on wire racks.
Store with waxed paper or transparent wrap between layers in container with tight-fitting cover.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream potatoes until smooth.
Combine with other ingredients. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn heat down to 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift in the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan. Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Place frozen broccoli in colander and run hot water over it to soften.
Mix broccoli, butter, cottage cheese, eggs and onions together.
Add cornbread mix and stir.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken picatta
directions: Mix flour, paprika and garlic.
Mix egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Melt butter in pan. Dip chicken in egg, then flour. Brown chicken on both sides.
Add instant bouillon with 2 tablespoons lemon juice and water.
Add liquid to chicken. Cover and cook on low 20 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Make stuffing according to directions; set aside.
Mix rice, milk, mushroom pieces and soup in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on mixture.
Put stuffing on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tours house salad
directions: Toast seeds on a cookie sheet at about 325° until golden brown.
Toss and combine above ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a food processor; blend until vegetables are diced very fine.
Add this mixture to dressing mix. Mix together and chill.
Make ahead of time to allow flavors to marinate.

title: indiana's best pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in pie shells at 450° for 10 minutes, then set oven on 350° and bake until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Rub clove of garlic throughout on the inside of a warm fondue pot.
Warm wine; do not allow to boil.
Stir in cheeses until smooth.
Mix together cornstarch and Kirsch until smooth and add to the cheese mixture.
Prior to serving, add pepper and nutmeg. Use good crusty French bread.
Tear off chunks and dip into the cheese.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch layer cake pans.
Put cake mix, oil and eggs in mixing bowl; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed with electric beater.
Combine gelatin and flour; set aside.
Drain strawberries well; reserve 1/2 cup of syrup.
Add gelatin mixture, strawberries and reserved syrup to batter in bowl; beat for 1 minute.
Turn into pans.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Fill and frost with Strawberry Frosting.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Delicious.

title: chess pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and melt butter.
Mix all ingredients (eggs, melted butter, vanilla, sugar and pecans) together.
It is best to use a fork.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dortha's holiday salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water, plus 1 cup cold juice from the canned fruit.
Let this mixture chill until it starts to thicken, then add fruit and walnuts. Drain the fruit cocktail before adding to the mixture.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Combine pecans, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave for 1 or 2 more minutes.
Pecans should be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool for 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Peanuts also work well in this recipe.

title: orange fun pops
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into ice cube trays.
Put a drinking straw (which has been cut in 1/2) into each cube; freeze.

title: old fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Can use original or roasted honey nut peanut butter.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble; drain. Spoon beef into a baking dish (approximately 8-inch square) and top with sauce and cheese.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients in order in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes, then serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and butter generously.
Line with soda crackers.
Meanwhile, melt real butter and add brown sugar.
Cook approximately 3 minutes, until well mixed.
Pour over crackers and bake 5 minutes in 425° oven.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over the cracker mixture.
Allow chips to melt, then spread evenly.
If nuts are desired, sprinkle nuts before spreading the chips.
Allow this candy to sit overnight before cutting.
A pizza cutter gives the best results.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, water and pineapple into a saucepan and heat until Jell-O has completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cube cream cheese and add to Jell-O mixture.
Stir until melted.
Let it cool slightly and then add Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Mix well sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, add mandarin oranges, crushed pineapple, pineapple tidbits, Cool Whip, marshmallows and cherries.

title: quick alfredo sauce
directions: Melt 1/4 cup oleo in saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup flour gradually. Stir constantly until smooth.
Add chicken bouillon cubes to water and dissolve.
Add to first mixture.
Add half and half.
Add parsley.
Stir until
thickened.
Stir in Parmesan cheese until melted.
Serve over fettucine.

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook
hamburger
and
sausage and drain off excess fat. To the
hamburger sausage, add diced onion, drained mushrooms and Velveeta cheese.
Mix well.
On cookie sheet lay out bread and spoon on mixture (approximately 1 tablespoon) each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers (sides and bottom). Wrap aluminum foil around outside of spring-form pan (3 inches above spring-form).
Mix all ingredients and pour in prepared pan. Refrigerate for several hours and top with strawberry pie filling.

title: hot tuna pocket
directions: Mix tuna fish, mayo, onion, celery and grated carrots together.
Just use as much onion, celery and grated carrots as you like.
Stuff into pocket bread and put 1 ounce fat-free cheese (I like Swiss) in each pocket.
Bake at 375° for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut pocket bread in half.
Makes 4 good size pockets.

title: meat loaf with a flair
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs slightly with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape meat in oval loaf.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Spread remaining ketchup on top.
Bake 50 minute at 400 degrees.

title: strawberry-rhubarb crisp
directions: Oven Method:
Wash rhubarb; cut off and discard leaves.
Cut rhubarb stalks into 3/4-inch pieces.
You'll need 5 cups diced rhubarb.
Arrange rhubarb in greased 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with strawberry gelatin powder.
Combine flour, sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat, about 2 minutes.
Stir butter into flour mixture and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.

title: old english pecan pudding pie
directions: Blend syrup with pudding.
Mix in bowl.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg, stirring to blend.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 55 minutes.

title: nut crescent cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, shape like crescents.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hardanger lefse
directions: Roll out thin and bake on lefse grill until light brown. Stays soft and does not need to be kept in cloth.
Serve with brown sugar or butter, creamed and cut into squares.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon, use additional mayonnaise if needed to moisten.
Cook bacon and crumble on top of casserole.	Pour a small amount of bacon grease over casserole to season.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Mix milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla in large saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture thickens and is golden (about 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread, stirring occasionally.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt butter in pie plate.
Combine flour, salt and milk in bowl; mix well.
Pour excess butter into flour mixture and add eggs.
Pour batter into pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, until puffy and lightly browned.
May serve with lemon juice and powdered sugar glaze.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortilla chips
directions: Cut tortillas into 8 pie-shape wedges.
Place on a sprayed cookie sheet.
Spray tortilla chips, then shake your choice of optional topping onto top of chips.
Place in oven at 400° and bake for 10 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mash cream cheese with fork until smooth.
Add picante sauce and onions.
Mix well.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Lay in pan, seam side down, and put in refrigerator until chilled.
Slice in about 1/4-inch slices.

title: carrot-bacon skillet
directions: Two 16 oz. each cans whole carrots, drained, can be substituted for fresh carrots.

title: poor man's sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter (or butter and Crisco) and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Beat, but do not overbeat. Pour into greased and floured stem pan.
Place in a cold oven, turn to 275° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Pour
half
of	the
oysters
into a buttered casserole dish. Layer
half
of
the crumbs, remaining oysters and then the remaining
cracker crumbs.	Make a sauce of the butter and half and
half
cream.
Pour over the mixture and cook at 350° for 1/2 hour or until it bubbles.
This makes a big dish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large saucepan, brown salt pork and sausage with half of the garlic over medium heat; chop meat into fine pieces as it browns.
Add tomato sauce and tomato juice, stirring over medium heat.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and brown sugar, remaining garlic and spices.
Bring to a simmer, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat, cover and stir occasionally.
Simmer up to 4 hours.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Dissolve tomato soup in water.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cheese filled triangles
directions: Crumble cheese in a small bowl, and mash with a fork.
Stir in eggs, chives and white pepper until well mixed.
Cut phyllo sheets lengthwise into 3 equal strips.
Cover with waxed paper, then with a damp towel to keep them from drying out.
Using 2 layers of phyllo at a time, place 1 heaping tsp. filling on one end of strip.
Fold end over end in a triangular shape to opposite sides (like a flag).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Repeat. Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Brush triangles with margarine.
Bake until puffed and golden, about 20 minutes.

title: breakfast brunch souffle
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage.
Mix together all ingredients except bread cubes, meat and cheese.
In buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, lay bread cubes.
Sprinkle meat over cubes and cheese over meat.
Pour other ingredients over these layers.
Let settle in refrigerator overnight (cover pan).
Set out for 15 minutes, then bake for one hour at 350°, uncovered.
Cool for a few minutes.
Cut in approximately 12 pieces.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Place layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: strawberry cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix well.
Mix in thawed strawberries.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or fruit.

title: chili dog casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a 9X13 inch baking dish. Tear or cut up the hot dog buns and arrange the pieces in the bottom of the dish evenly. Slice the hot dogs into bite-size pieces and layer the pieces over the buns. Pour chili over the hot dogs, sprinkle with the chopped onion, then drizzle some mustard over the chili and the onion. Top off with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: quick mexican dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, chili and then cheese.
Melt in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.
In saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with margarine and milk, stirring until smooth.
Spread over cake, then spread remaining batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts. Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until cake springs back.
Cool. Garnish as desired.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients into a soft doughy mixture.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 40 lightly browned balls to be served hot.

title: crescent sausage and cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large triangles and place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up the sides to form crust, sealing perforations with fingers.
Place sausage slices over crust. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cut in 24 pieces.

title: "best" sugar cookies
directions: * To make sour milk, mix 2 tablespoons vinegar to 1 cup milk.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: (1) Up to one hour before serving, combine coleslaw mix, green onions, noodles (save serving mix for the dressing), almonds, and sunflower kernels in a salad bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: beef lentil soup
directions: Cut the beef across the grain into 1/2-inch slices.
Sprinkle with freshly ground pepper.
In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add beef and saute until lightly browned all over. Sprinkle with flour; stir well.
Saute 4 to 5 minutes to cook flour.
Add water and stir well.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Add celery, carrots, onions, lentils and thyme.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add lemon juice and correct pepper, if needed.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine; add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Make into tiny balls, about 1 tsp. Place on wax paper. Place in freezer.

title: death by chocolate
directions: This dessert should be layered in a tall
glass bowl.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, adding nuts and raw apples last.
Grease and flour 1 large pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: anthony's beans
directions: Mix beans, cheese, garlic salt and mushrooms.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix thick enough to roll in hands. Spoon 1 tablespoon on tips of fingers. Press cherry in middle and roll. Place on cookie sheet and chill.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Use large 9 x 13-inch baking dish and layer first 4 ingredients in order listed.
Pour celery soup over all.
Then melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over.
Cover with foil and bake approximately 1 hour at 425°.

title: old-fashioned scalloped apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 1-quart casserole dish. Pare, core
and slice apples. Place in the buttered casserole and sprinkle
with cinnamon, salt, lemon juice and water. Dot with vanilla.
Mix the brown sugar, flour and butter together and spread
over the apples and bake for 30 minutes. Best when served warm.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set a few hours before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add white sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Beat eggs lightly and add, then add flour and soda, sifted together.
Mix well.
Take a piece the size of a walnut, roll into a ball and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Place boneless breast of chicken in a baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour mixture on top of chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Baste occasionally.

title: baked apples
directions: Take large red apples, core and pare.
Fill apples with mincemeat and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with hard sauce.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion in pan, then push aside and brown ground beef.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Can add pieces of Polish sausage, if desired.
Serve with hot rolls or corn bread.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Mix soup, milk, pepper and salt; set aside.
Place layer of sliced potato in greased baking dish.
Add layer of ham, then onion slices.
Repeat until all is used.
Pour soup mixture over. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover, top with cheese and paprika.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: grandma's swedish pancakes
directions: Beat all together with mixer or rotary beater until smooth. Pour into frying pan and cook on one side until bubbly.
Then turn and cook until golden brown.
Put butter or sugar on; roll up and eat.

title: microwaved baked salmon steaks
directions: Melt butter on High about 30 seconds.
Add lemon juice, salt and
pepper.
Pour	over
salmon.
Top with onion slices. Cook on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.	Serve with lemon wedges.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Jimmy Dean regular or mild sausage is best. Cook, crumble and drain. Place bread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs, milk, mustard, onion powder, salt and pepper. Pour evenly over bread and cheese. Sprinkle cooked sausage, mushrooms and tomatoes over the top. Cover and chill overnight.

title: rice pudding
directions: In 6 qt. oven-safe bowl, mix rice, sugar, butter, vanilla, and milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg and place in 350 degree oven for 1-1/2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.
Add 1 c. raisins at the last stirring.

title: puffed broccoli
directions: Put cooked broccoli in small broiler proof dish or pan.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cheese and mayonnaise.
Spoon over broccoli.
Broil 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: tater, ham n broccoli bake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 baking dish, layer the first 3 ingredients in the order listed. Combine the soup, milk and mayonnaise and whisk until smooth. Pour this mixture over first 3 ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks until light; add corn, seasonings and flour. Stir to blend.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop by spoonful into skillet of hot fat.
Cook until brown, turning once.

title: cheesy salmon rotini
directions: *If using tuna, drain all liquid and use 2 1/4 cups milk.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add condensed milk while mixing; stir until blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla extract; beat well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before topping with cherry pie filling or strawberries.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy frypan, add onions and cook until soft and caramelized.
Add wine and sherry.
Bring to boil.
Add beef stock, Worcestershire, thyme and bay leaf.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Top each serving with toasted bread and grated Gruyere or Swiss cheese.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Beat all of the ingredients together.
Put aside for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bring a large pan of salted water to a boil and add bits of the mixture by placing on a cutting board and cutting bits into the water or forcing through a slotted spoon.
Remove from the water when the dumpling floats to the top of the water.
These may be drained and put aside to be turned in a pan in melted butter to warm.
If this sounds too difficult, some food shops sell "Spatzli" produced by Knorr, usually in the pasta section.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and refrigerate several hours. Slice off top third of bread, hollow out the inside.
Fill with spinach mixture.
Place raw vegetables and crackers around bread. Bread from inside may be used for dipping too.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients and stir in. Blend in walnuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop rounded tablespoons 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes until delicately browned.
When cool, frost with Burnt Sugar Glaze. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken and rice foil dinner
directions: Place chicken on a 14 inch square of heavy-duty foil.
Mix can of condensed cream of mushroom soup with 2/3 cup uncooked instant rice.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Seal the foil package and place on grill 5 inches above coals.
Cook about 40 minutes, turning once.

title: diabetic pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Beat whipping cream and refrigerate.
Put a couple of tablespoons of pineapple in cream cheese and beat until fluffy. Pour off about 1/4 of juice from pineapple so pie won't be too sloppy.
After beating cream cheese, fold in whipping cream with the Equal.
Then add crushed pineapple and vanilla.
Be sure your pie crust gets good and brown and cool before filling it.
Chill at least 3 hours.
The longer it sets, the more flavorable it is.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Place the cabbage, salt, sugar, vinegar and caraway seed in a large saucepan; cover with water.
Simmer for 30 minutes until cabbage is soft.
Serve hot.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and seasoning and boil.
Add vegetables. Boil 20 minutes (plus).
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: hungarian butternut cookies(a holiday treat)
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla, salt and egg yolk with electric mixer until smooth. Combine flour with pecans and gradually beat into flour mixture. Wrap in waxed paper, then plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Immediately place in bowl with powdered sugar and roll around to coat. Makes 4 dozen.

title: ready mix pie crust
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
When crumbly, place in plastic bucket or plastic bags.
Do not refrigerate or freeze.
Just take enough mix out for pie.
Add a little cold water.
Roll out and place in pan.
Will stay good for a year.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat egg and almond extract.
Add to butter mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Chill dough 2 hours.

title: fat free chocolate torte
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, liquid Butter Buds and cereal. Press in bottom of glass dish.
Mix Dream Whip with 1 cup skimmed milk until thick.
Add cream cheese and Equal.
Mix instant pudding with 3 cups skimmed milk and let thicken.
Spread half of Dream Whip mixture over crust.
Then put chocolate pudding over that and spread the rest of the Dream Whip mixture on top. Sprinkle with Grape Nuts and refrigerate.

title: mandarin orange cheesecake
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool cake.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread coconut and chopped pecans on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake batter according to package directions. Pour over coconut and pecans.
Melt butter and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat.
When melted, stir in confectioners sugar; stir until well blended.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey glazed snack mix
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cereal, pretzels and pecans; set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in honey and blend. Pour over cereal, spread on cookie sheet.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs, 1 cup chopped pecans and butter together (mixture will be thick).
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla together. Spread over chocolate layer and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip, chopped pecans, chocolate chips and coconut.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Stir until berries are thawed. Add pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour 1/2 mixture in dish and congeal.
Add cream cheese to remaining mixture and pour over congealed mixture.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Toss all together and set aside in bowl.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, rice, soup, cheese, milk and water in 2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice water and let stand 4 hours.
Drain and press out all liquid. Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in drained vegetables and simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: pumpkin cheese torte
directions: Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Pour over crust of flour, butter or margarine and pecans.
Press in pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake 25 minutes.
Combine pudding, pumpkin, milk and water.
Beat 3 minutes.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold in pumpkin mixture. Spoon over cheese mixture.
Top with whipped topping.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a medium bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk and vanilla; stir.
Pour batter evenly over peaches.
Top with pats of margarine or butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8. Prep time:
15 minutes.

title: pecans scandia
directions: Fold sugar into egg whites; mix in pecans. Melt butter in jellyroll pan in a 325° oven; spoon nut mixture over butter. Bake 30 minutes at 325°, stirring every 10 minutes. Sprinkle with salt as nuts bake. Cool. Makes 4 cups. Can do ahead.

title: mini turkey loaves
directions: Mix thoroughly
1/4 cup of soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/8 teaspoon each of pepper, sage and thyme. Shape firmly into 6 mini loaves.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3 cups hot water.
Cool.
Add drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill in 9 x 12-inch flat dish until firm.
Heat pineapple juice in top of double boiler. Add flour and sugar to beaten egg.
Mix with juice and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold into whipped cream. Spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle cheese generously over all.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: children's play dough
directions: Mix oil in boiling water.
Add food coloring. Mix dry ingredients together and add to liquid mix.
Mix well.
Cool slightly, then knead.
Store in airtight container or Ziploc bags.

title: blue cheese dressing(low-fat)
directions: Add buttermilk to Blue cheese until mixture is thick.
Add sour cream.
Add more buttermilk until desired thickness.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash while hot.
Work all the sugar into the potatoes that they will take.
Pat into a thin layer, cover with peanut butter and roll.
Let stand, then slice.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: springtime dessert
directions: Dissolve jello; cool slightly.
Stir in evaporated milk; chill until mixture is as thick as unbeaten egg white.
Fold in all other ingredients.
Pour into long dish.
Chill.

title: fresh apple pastry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, stir flour and salt together.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Beat egg yolk lightly with fork in a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to egg yolk to make 2/3 cup.
Stir milk into flour mixture; mix with fork to blend, stirring until mixture holds together and cleans sides of bowl.
Divide the dough into 2 parts.
Roll half of dough to line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Place dough in pan, pressing down lightly to form bottom crust.
Sprinkle bottom crust with corn flakes.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Blend graham crackers, sugar and 4 tablespoons butter.
Line spring-form pan.
In large bowl, mash cottage cheese.
Add cream cheese.
Mix until creamy.
Add sugar.
Continue beating.
Add eggs.
Reduce speed to low.
Add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add butter and sour cream.
Blend on low speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Turn off oven and let stand in oven for 2 hours.

title: onion pie
directions: One meal item - like pizza.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the beans and soup in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Put onion rings on top and bake for 5 to 8 minutes longer.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine in bowl and serve with fresh fruit.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix these ingredients together with a package of corned beef. Mold into a ball.
Chop another package of corned beef and put on the outside of ball.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Great for a snack.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a blender or food processor, mix coarsely chopped onions and beef.
