Add cubed cream cheese, m. s. g. and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 or 2 nights to allow flavors to blend.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken breast into small pieces and saute in butter until cooked through (use a large pot).
Pour in both soups, chopped green onions and the chiles, rinsed and drained.
You can add some jalapeno peppers if you like things a little hotter.
Add both cheeses (leaving 1/2 cup of each to sprinkle on top later).
Add sour cream and mix together until combined.
Spoon 1 or 2 tablespoons of mixture into tortilla.
Roll.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread remaining mixture over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° (covered) for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: buster bars
directions: Step 1:
Soften ice cream in large bowl.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion into small pieces. Toss the vegetables with bacon bits and Cheddar cheese. Mix mayo and Italian dressing together, then combine with remaining ingredients. Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Soak bread crumbs with milk.
Add eggs (beaten lightly), butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese.
Mix altogether and bake at 350° until brown.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over flank steak and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning often.
Grill steak over charcoal, basting with marinade.

title: rice and peas
directions: Pick and wash peas.
Boil peas and garlic in two pints water. Boil gently so that the peas are softened without being turned into a soup like condition.
Add additional seasoning to taste if necessary, adding scallion in the last few minutes.

title: mama watts' easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over peaches and bake at 350° until you think it is done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Top with Cheddar cheese and crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: soft flantas
directions: Boil fryer until done; bone fryer and shred thin.
Heat oil hot, then take tortillas and run through hot oil.
Leave tortillas soft.
Drain tortillas.
Spread sour cream on tortilla; sprinkle prepared chicken.
Add lettuce and tomatoes.
Roll up.
They are ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream milk, vanilla, sugar and shortening; add eggs and bananas.
Combine salt, soda and baking powder to flour.
Add to banana mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 3 loaf pans and bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Freezes real good.

title: no fat seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Place over rapidly boiling water, beating constantly at high speed of electric mixer for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until of spreading consistency.

title: macaroni bake
directions: About 50 minutes before serving:
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 2-quart casserole.
Cook macaroni; drain.
In casserole stir all ingredients.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Stew
chicken	until
tender.	Debone	chicken.
Saute onion in olive
oil.
Add
tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies, mushroom soup, celery seed, oregano and salt.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add
chicken and cook a few minutes longer. Serve over cooked
yellow
rice.
Cook the rice in the chicken broth.

title: fruit sparkle
directions: *Dilute frozen concentrate as directed and freeze in ice cube trays.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and seasonings in fat or oil until transparent. Add tomato sauce and shrimp to that mixture. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: *watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with pineapple and juice.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.
Use small 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch casserole dish.
Serves 15.

title: relish plate dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: individual cream cheese cakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, nutmeg and vanilla.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of paper muffin cup.
Fill 2/3 full and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Top each one with cherry pie filling.

title: stuffed eggplant - "hasami age"(servings:  6)
directions: Remove stem of eggplant and cut lengthwise in half, but not all of the way through.
Open and soak in salt water.
Saute onion.
Mix ground meat, onion, bread crumbs, salt and water. Divide into 8 parts.
Wipe off moisture from eggplant.
Sprinkle cornstarch on cut surface.
Place layer of meat mixture between eggplant halves.
Sprinkle cornstarch around meat.
Heat oil and deep fry over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Cook until meat is well done.
Eat with grated ginger and soy sauce.

title: homecoming chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Set aside.
Combine milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Add sugar mixture and stir to mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, beat egg whites, then add vanilla and slowly add sugar. Beat until stiff peaks form.
Remove pie from oven when center is set.
Spoon beaten egg whites onto top of pie, smoothing to edge of crust.
Return to oven to brown meringue, about 5 minutes.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: Mix with pastry blender in large bowl to coarse crumbs.
Store in airtight container for 6 weeks.
Freeze for 6 months.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Stir thoroughly.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add all at once oil, eggs, water and pumpkin. Mix in pecans.
Pour batter in 4 greased 8 x 4-inch pans.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: golden vegetable casserole
directions: Trim cauliflower; separate into flowerets.
Slice carrots into 1-inch pieces.
Combine vegetables and water in saucepan.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain.
Place half the vegetables in a greased 4-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half the soup, then half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour butter over cheese.
Cover; bake at 200° for 1 hour or until cheese is melted and sauce is hot. Serves 20.

title: paul's bean casserole
directions: In a medium casserole dish, mix together the beans, onions, soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle cheese over top and then fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rizogalo(rice pudding)
directions: Boil rice until almost done.
Drain.
Heat milks on low heat. Add
rice,
stir
and
simmer on low heat until rice is tender. Set
aside.
Beat
eggs
until very thick.
Add sugar and continue to beat, adding cornstarch gradually to mixture. Slowly pour egg mixture into rice mixture.
Return to heat for a minute or two until slightly thickened, being careful not to cook too long
or it will not set.
Pour into serving bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cajun-style catfish
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
In medium bowl, mix orange juice, lemon juice, lime juice, rice vinegar, garlic, jalapeno peppers, chili powder and black pepper.
Arrange each fish on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Bring edges upward to form a bowl.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of sauce over each fish.
Pinch top of foil together, leaving small space for steam to escape.
Cook fish for 8 to 10 minutes in foil packets or until flakes easily with fork.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with fish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream hot dish
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add beef and brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Place noodles in layer over meat.
Combine juice and seasonings.
Pour over noodles.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer over low for 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and mushrooms.
Heat through.

title: tomato cream pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Cook onion, zucchini and garlic in oil 3 minutes.
Add meat and cook until browned.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
To meat add liquid; cook on high 5 minutes. Add cream; cook 8 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently. Stir in tomatoes and pasta; heat through.
Serve with grated cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, milk, horseradish, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and cream cheese and process until smooth.
Spoon mixture into bowl and add Cheddar cheese and crab meat.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with crackers or breadsticks.

title: little holiday raisin logs
directions: Mix in large bowl margarine, sugar, vanilla, salt and flour. Mix well.
Roll dough into little logs, 1/2-inch wide x 2-inches long.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes; don't brown.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Beat oleo or butter in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour evenly into three 9-inch cake pans, greased and lined with wax paper (grease paper).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Be sure they are done but do not overbake.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add Spanish rice and chili beans.
Stir and simmer until hot.
Add crushed Doritos on top.
Layer cheese on top of Doritos.
Cover and allow cheese to melt over low heat.

title: rice and pea casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
together
in large casserole dish and bake in 350° oven 1 1/2 hours.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order, except cheese.
Pour half of the batter in a greased baking pan, then layer with half the cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey easy
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter baking dish or individual dishes. Combine turkey and next 6 ingredients.
Mix together soup and milk. Add 1/2 of it to turkey mixture.
Pour in dish or dishes.
Spread remaining soup on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 350°. Check pie at 45 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pour the chicken broth into a small saucepan; stir in the bay leaf and white pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Melt the butter in an ovenproof 2-quart saucepan.
Add onion; cook over medium heat until transparent. Add the rice to the onion; stir until rice is very hot and well coated.
Carefully pour the boiling broth over the rice mixture, stirring well. Bring to a full boil.
Cover and bake for approximately 15 minutes, or until the liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender.
Remove the pan from the oven; gently stir in parsley.

title: spiced bread crumb pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 1/2 hour.
Cream the butter and sugar together, add molasses, flour sifted with the spices and soda, then the raisins.
Add this to the bread crumbs and milk.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt and flavoring, then add flour and baking powder.
Melt margarine in milk that has been heated to boiling; add to batter.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into prepared pans soon as mixed.
Bake in tube pan for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven or in a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken and ziti casserole
directions: Stir together Prego, ziti, chicken and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in cold water until pastry forms a ball.
Yields 1 to 2 pie crusts.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender. Drain well. Add all other ingredients except meal. Add more bread crumbs, if necessary, to handle easily.
Form into oblong croquettes and roll into meal. Fry in deep fat until light brown.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Brown meat, set aside.
Saute onion, carrot and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine for about 10 minutes.
Add chicken broth, potatoes and sauteed vegetables.
Cook about 15 minutes until potatoes are done.
Put 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet with 1/4 cup flour.
Make a roux.
Put in vegetables and meat.
Turn on low and stir in cheese and milk until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with corn bread.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: While cake is warm spread top with mixture made from juice of lemons mixed with sugar.
Broil glaze until hot and bubbly.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and spices) in a separate bowl; alternate with cup of liquid.
Add raisins, currants and cherries; this is a very heavy batter and you might want to literally get your hands into it.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Saute onion and butter.
Add to first mixture.
Sprinkle in hot water and mix well.
Slit pocket in chops.
Stuff loosely with apple mixture.
Close with skewers.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion; add salt, garlic, catsup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Press each biscuit into a 4 x 4-inch square.
Fill with beef mixture; fold over to form a triangle.
Seal edges with a fork.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with butter before baking.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Place bread crumbs on bottom of casserole dish.
Add crumbled sausage on top of bread.
Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Add egg and milk mixture.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt lucille's party franks
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until glazed.

title: e-z cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Slice onions, chop peppers and cook until brown in butter; add meat, salt, pepper and mustard and stir constantly until meat is seared well.
Butter baking dish and add alternate layers of meat and rice until all is used.
Pour tomatoes over.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: diet pie
directions: Make pudding according to package.
Cover with Cool Whip lite.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all vegetables and chicken in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with poultry seasonings.
Stir in soup and milk until well mixed. Place in an unlined 9 1/2-inch pie plate.
Spread mixture evenly. Place pie crust over pie plate.
Slit crust (4 lines) for air to escape.
Seal edges of pie.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: zesty dressing
directions: In covered blender container, blend at medium speed until smooth and slightly thickened.
Stir before serving.
Makes one cup.
Contains 5 calories per tablespoon.

title: curry canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on toasted bread rounds.
Broil until bubbly.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients and let stand 5 to 10 minutes. To the yeast water, add 2 cups flour and all other ingredients. Mix with mixer 2 minutes.
Beat other 2 cups flour by hand.
Let stand until doubled in size.
Roll out and cut rolls.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise again and cook 15 minutes at 425°.

title: granny chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick. Pour in baked pie shell.
Put meringue made from egg whites on top.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Put into a 10 x 15-inch greased pan and bake 15 minutes at 400°. Remove and lower temperature to 350°.
Spread the spaghetti sauce over the noodles. Add the browned hamburger. Add the pepperoni slices and top with the cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir well. Microwave 8 to 12 minutes or until mixture reaches hard-ball stage (260°).

title: squash dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread as usual; let cool and crumble up.
Add cooked squash, oleo, onions, cream of chicken soup, salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chef's salad
directions: Into a large salad bowl, tear lettuce and romaine into bite-size pieces (about 12 cups).
Reserve a few strips of meat and cheese.
Toss remaining meat and cheese strips, the onion and celery with salad greens.
Blend mayonnaise and French dressing; pour over salad and toss.
Garnish with reserved meat and cheese strips, the olives, egg slices and tomato wedges.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Beat cake mix with the pie filling, eggs and sour cream using a fork.
Beat
1 minute.
Pour into an ungreased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes and cool.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and shake well until sugar is dissolved.
Use on tossed lettuce salad.

title: good-for-you muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine oats, flours, brown sugar, oat bran, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add fruit and Grape-Nuts.
Stir to coat with flour mixture.
In a 2 cup measure, combine milk, oil and egg whites.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Spoon batter into cups, filling cups full.
Bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly on wire rack.

title: bread and butter pickles(for weight watchers)
directions: Cut cucumbers in paper-thin slices.
Let onion, peppers, cucumber and salt
stand
covered with ice water for 3 hours in large container;
drain.
Make
a syrup from sweetener, vinegar and spices.
When
sweetener is dissolved, add drained pickles. Bring to a
boil, but do not boil.
Pack in sterilized jars and process in
boiling
water
for
5 minutes.
Pickles taste best when chilled completely before serving.

title: e-z tortillas(makes about 10 large tortillas)
directions: Mix flour and salt together in a bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour in oil and water.
Stir with a fork until the dough clumps together in a ball.
Scatter flour on wax paper.
Break off balls of dough (the size of a golf ball).
Roll them in flour. Flatten with hand, turning often.
Roll each tortilla out thin and cook quickly on preheated hot griddle (using no oil) until brown spots appear on tortillas.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Serve with apple slices.

title: jello icicles
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly, then add 2 cups cold water. Stir and pour into ice cube trays. Freeze. Makes 19 cubes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; add zucchini.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to full boil; turn off. Mix in peanut butter until melted. Add corn flakes. Mix until well coated. Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered foil.

title: chicken fried steak & gravy
directions: Heat oil in large skillet (electric works best).
Mix beaten eggs with in shallow bowl.
Put flour on flat plate.
Salt and pepper steaks.
Dip each steak in flour, then egg mixture, then back into flour to coat.
Place in skillet and cook for approximately 8 - 10 minutes.
Turn when browned on each side, cook to golden brown.
Remove steaks from skillet to plate covered with paper towel to drain.

title: chicken casserole 2
directions: Boil chicken until tender and pull apart or cut in pieces. Put chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together and spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top and press into mixture.
Cut up margarine and put on top.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Light and dark meat may be used, if desired.

title: monkey cake
directions: Melt butter and 1 cup sugar; keep hot, not boiling.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Add biscuits, shake and coat 2 packages at a time.
(Use a bowl with a lid.)
Place the 2 packages in layers in Bundt pan and pour 1/2 of butter and sugar mixture over it.
Repeat with other packages. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mama's chicken pot pie
directions: Cook a hen
in	a pot of water (6 to 7 cups) until meat falls off
the
bone.
Add
salt	and pepper to taste.
Remove chicken. Skin,
bone
and
chop
meat
into bite size pieces. Strain broth and remove some chicken fat.
To 2 cups of flour add shortening and
enough
water	to make a dough resembling pie crust.
Knead on	floured
countertop
and roll out thin. Cut into 3 x 3-inch squares
and let stand for an hour.
Mama always said to let
the dough
get	tough.	Boil stock.
Peel dumplings off counter
and drop in the rapidly boiling stock, working quickly.
After	all squares are in pot, add chicken. Stir gently and let boil for 5 minutes.
Take pot off heat and let sit.
Should
be consistency of stew, not clumped together or balled up.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a small low casserole dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onions and/or chopped tomato, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.
Makes 2 cups.

title: favorite tuna dip
directions: Cream the first three ingredients.
Add tuna fish, stirring well.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Serve with dipping chips.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put cake mix, jello, oil and flour in bowl and beat 2 minutes. While beating, add 1/2 cup cold water and eggs.
Fold in strawberries.
Bake as per instructions on cake mix.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: nut cake
directions: Dissolve teaspoon soda in molasses.
Mix flour, raisins and pecans.
Beat eggs, butter and sugar.
Add wine and spices and add to flour mixture and molasses mixture.
Bake 4 hours at 250°.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add in vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and oatmeal.
(Put oatmeal in blender in small amounts.
Blend until powdered.)
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil one hour tomatoes, green peppers, onions and vinegar. Add sugar and salt.
Cook slowly another hour.
Add spices.
Stir. Put sauce in canning jars, process in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: diabetic pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put into a well buttered 9-inch pie pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done at 350°.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: irish potato candy
directions: Peel and boil potato.
Mix thoroughly with sugar until you have a ball like pie crust.
With rolling pin, roll out to look like pie crust.
Spread on top with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll out 1/4-inch to 1/3-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugars.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
After baking, store sealed to keep soft.
(I roll them in balls, and flatten them.)

title: aunt jean's jewels
directions: Put milk and sorghum
in double boiler and let thicken. Add remaining
ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: corn creole(low-fat)
directions: Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart pot.
Add onion and green pepper; stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.

title: curry chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese, milk, curry powder and lemon juice.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on bottom; top with cooked broccoli.
Pour sauce over and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Top with toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: apple bake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg, and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients of flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Fold in apples and pour into a 9 X 13 pan. Mix brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle on top of batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir in butter while still hot.
Put in a buttered 10-inch baking pan.
Spread cottage cheese over the spaghetti.
Cook meat, onion and peppers.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato paste and rest of ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy baked ham
directions: Place pineapple slices on ham and pour Coke over entire ham. Cover in foil and bake until heated thoroughly at 350°, for 2 to 3 hours.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions; put in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spread evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: corn scallop
directions: Warm milk to about 120°.
Pour it over the crumbs and soak. Have the corn ground through food mill.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking pan.
Put small bits of butter or cream over top and bake to a light brown.

title: easy elegant chicken
directions: Lightly grease pan.
Place chicken in bottom. Mix soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Layer cheese, then dry herb stuffing on top.
Drizzle melted margarine over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scallops with spaghetti(spaghetti e cape sante)
directions: Cook
spaghetti
according to package directions.
Wash and dry the scallops.
Dredge the scallops in the flour.
In a large frying pan, heat the olive oil over high heat until very hot.
Add the
floured scallops and fry quickly while turning them
until lightly
golden.
Remove
scallops
and
add
the garlic, parsley,
wine,
basil,
salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture
is bubbly.
Add scallops and toss.
Remove from heat and spoon over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: laurel's picadillo
directions: Brown meat, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes and sauce.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar and capers and cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Add spices, raisins, almonds and olives. Heat 5 minutes more.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add spices, milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts and gets thick.

title: positively sinful brownies
directions: Melt together chocolate and margarine.
Mix in powdered sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Spread on cooled brownies.
Refrigerate. These brownies freeze well.

title: pina colada
directions: Mix in blender until thick and frosty.
tags: frozen ice cubes of coconut milk

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: pasta with pesto
directions: Toast pine nuts. Lay out in single layer in toaster oven tray and push "toast". Boil pasta for recommended time. While pasta is boiling, nuke rehydrated tomatoes for 30 seconds or just until warm.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and water. Let cool.
Stir in vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Add chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar slowly.
In separate bowl, mix rest of ingredients.
Fold into egg whites.
Pour into deep buttered pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream and sliced peaches, drained thawed strawberries or any other kind of fruit.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by tablespoonful into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: mrs. hughes' congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in a little cold juice of pineapple.
Drain remaining juice and juice from cherries.
Add to gelatine.
Heat. Let stand until cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Scoop out meat and chop up.
Set aside shell of eggplant.
Saute garlic, eggplant meat and onion in pan with a small amount of oil until onion is transparent and soft, over medium heat.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fold in remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Place half the mixture in a mold or dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread on sour cream and spoon on remaining Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: grandma's cornbread
directions: Combine first four ingredients, set aside. Beat eggs, add butter and milk. Then add to the dry ingredients. Beat until smooth and pour into a greased 9x13 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma's orange cake
directions: Place grated orange rind in the juice and let it stand while mixing the cake.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Beat egg yolks until thick and creamy and add to the creamed mixture.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the liquid (orange juice and water).
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into 2 well-greased and floured layer cake pans (two 9-inch).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Mix margarine, onion flakes, poppy seeds and Worcestershire sauce in pot.
Let melt.
Cut in half party rolls.
Add ham slices and cheese slices.
Brush melted mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Set aside.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once. Blend with a spoon just until flour is all moistened.
Roll out and place in pie pan.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix together in order. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brownie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: white clam sauce spaghetti
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add parsley, oregano, olive oil and flour.
Stir until thick.
Add clams with its own juice, then add half and half cream.
Stir on medium heat until thickened; add mushrooms and simmer.
Serve over linguini noodles and sprinkle some Parmesan cheese on top.

Heat
water and butter to rolling boil. Stir in
flour.
Stir
vigorously over low heat about 1 minute, until mix
forms a ball.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at	a
time.
Beat	until
smooth.	Drop
by rounded teaspoon on ungreased
sheet.
Bake
25 to 30 minutes.	Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: lemon asparagas chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until brown. Add soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper. Bring to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the juice off the pineapple and mandarin oranges and mix with vanilla pudding.
Cook until thick according to box instructions.
Cool the pudding and add the fruit.
Slice the bananas and strawberries into fruit salad bowl.
Chill.

directions: *May use more of mayonnaise or sour cream to suit desired texture.
